WEBVTT

01:06.457 --> 01:09.547
ADAM: At first, they thought
there was something
wrong with my eyes.

01:11.288 --> 01:14.465
-OPHTHALMOLOGIST: One or two?
-One.

01:14.509 --> 01:17.512
ADAM: What I would have given for a classic case of glaucoma.

01:22.343 --> 01:23.648
OPHTHALMOLOGIST:
Okay, we're done.

01:24.823 --> 01:26.477
ADAM: 'Cause soon after...

01:28.958 --> 01:31.003
I started hearing the voices.

01:31.047 --> 01:33.832
-[VOICES WHISPERING]
-ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

01:33.876 --> 01:35.878
[INDISTINCT
WHISPERING CONTINUES]

01:38.750 --> 01:40.404
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

01:40.448 --> 01:42.624
I'm sure they told you
about the cooking.

01:42.667 --> 01:44.016
Call it what you want,

01:44.060 --> 01:47.368
a distraction,
self-medicating, whatever.

01:47.411 --> 01:49.979
But it was the only thing
that could make them shut up.

01:50.022 --> 01:51.023
[VOICES WHISPERING]

01:56.638 --> 01:59.075
[VOICES STOP]

01:59.119 --> 02:00.772
You okay?

02:00.816 --> 02:03.340
ADAM: And don't blame my mom for not figuring it out sooner.

02:04.863 --> 02:07.083
She had a lot goin' on
the past couple of years.

02:09.390 --> 02:12.175
When my dad decided
the whole fatherhood thing

02:12.219 --> 02:14.482
was a buzzkill
for his creativity,

02:16.353 --> 02:18.877
we had to take
the shit sandwich
we'd been served

02:18.921 --> 02:20.444
and make it edible.

02:25.101 --> 02:26.537
So, I cooked.

02:27.408 --> 02:28.626
And cooked.

02:29.888 --> 02:32.239
And the meals
became my contribution

02:32.282 --> 02:34.154
to our underdog story.

02:38.549 --> 02:41.378
Mmm. Sweetheart, it's delicious.

02:41.422 --> 02:43.641
ADAM: Plus,
I got really good at it.

02:43.685 --> 02:46.775
Mmm. It's just
the right amount of cumin.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.781
ADAM: And then Paul moved in.

02:56.741 --> 02:58.308
Mmm, it's interestin'.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.835
It's so good, honey. I love it.

03:03.879 --> 03:06.577
ADAM: Home, as I knew it,
became a thing of the past.

03:07.099 --> 03:08.188
PAUL: Uh...

03:08.231 --> 03:09.537
ADAM:
So I was getting out a lot.

03:09.580 --> 03:10.755
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

03:10.799 --> 03:12.061
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

03:14.281 --> 03:16.021
ADAM: Getting into
cooking school next fall

03:16.065 --> 03:17.806
was like an oasis

03:17.849 --> 03:20.243
from the dumpster fire
my brain was slowly becoming.

03:23.855 --> 03:26.597
I just needed to keep
my eye on the prize

03:26.641 --> 03:27.990
and bide my time.

03:32.255 --> 03:35.302
How hard could it be to hide
my burgeoning insanity

03:35.345 --> 03:38.479
from the unforgiving ecosystem that is high school?

03:38.522 --> 03:40.176
TODD: Check this out.

03:40.220 --> 03:41.960
We finally got invited
to one of Sarah's parties.

03:43.484 --> 03:46.226
We can't miss this one, man.
You're coming, right?

03:46.269 --> 03:47.444
I'll pick you up tonight?

03:49.185 --> 03:51.013
Who is that?

03:51.056 --> 03:52.710
Sarah? The love of my life?

03:52.754 --> 03:56.714
ADAM: I mean, for a while,
they were just voices.

03:56.758 --> 03:58.063
Yeah, right. Sarah.

04:00.501 --> 04:02.198
TEACHER: Now that
you've added the solute,

04:02.242 --> 04:05.984
please keep monitoring
the pH and the temperature.

04:06.028 --> 04:07.943
So, my parents are on
another trial separation,

04:07.986 --> 04:09.553
whatever.

04:09.597 --> 04:11.294
But I think I can guilt them
into letting me take the car.

04:11.338 --> 04:12.817
What do you say, dude,
for the party?

04:12.861 --> 04:15.167
And I'm telling you, man,
I think tonight's...

04:15.211 --> 04:17.257
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

04:17.300 --> 04:18.997
TODD: Adam, yo...

04:23.001 --> 04:24.351
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Over here.

04:28.050 --> 04:29.356
-What?
-TODD: Dude, careful,

04:29.399 --> 04:30.531
this shit's like lava.

04:30.574 --> 04:32.097
-I'm sorry.
-What're you doin'?

04:32.141 --> 04:33.664
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
Right here, Adam.

04:36.450 --> 04:39.104
-[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]
-[ADAM'S DARKNESS CHUCKLING]

04:39.148 --> 04:40.192
Todd.

04:40.236 --> 04:41.324
REBECCA: [ECHOES] Adam.

04:42.325 --> 04:43.631
We need to leave now.

04:54.032 --> 04:56.383
[SCREAMING] Oh, fuck!

04:56.861 --> 04:58.559
Adam!

04:58.602 --> 05:00.778
TEACHER: Everybody, clear away.
Just clear away.

05:01.518 --> 05:02.867
[ADAM BREATHING HEAVILY]

05:05.043 --> 05:06.610
[TODD GROANING]

05:15.489 --> 05:16.968
Don't worry, boss.

05:17.012 --> 05:18.187
We got this.

05:18.230 --> 05:20.668
-TODD: Do something, please!
-[WHISTLING]

05:20.711 --> 05:22.060
That hurts! It hurts!

05:22.800 --> 05:24.367
BODYGUARD: Hey, kid.

05:24.411 --> 05:25.760
-Kid!
-[BREATHING HEAVILY]

05:25.803 --> 05:27.936
You want us to protect
your scrawny ass, or what?

05:27.979 --> 05:28.980
Beat it.

05:31.243 --> 05:32.462
[MEN GRUNTING]

05:36.118 --> 05:37.772
Adam. Go.

05:38.816 --> 05:39.904
-GUARD: Just calm down.
-[GASPING]

05:39.948 --> 05:41.732
Calm down, son. Calm down.

05:41.776 --> 05:43.168
Just calm down, son.

05:43.212 --> 05:45.257
Calm. Just calm down.
It's okay.

05:45.301 --> 05:46.520
[ADAM GROANING]

05:46.563 --> 05:48.870
Just calm down, son. Calm down.

05:48.913 --> 05:50.393
-ADAM: Let go of me!
-GUARD: Just breathe.

05:51.046 --> 05:53.048
Just calm down.

05:53.091 --> 05:55.224
-Relax. Relax.
-[ADAM GASPING]

05:57.052 --> 05:59.707
ADAM: They called it
my first psychotic break.

06:01.099 --> 06:02.797
DOCTOR: Hello, Mister...

06:02.840 --> 06:05.060
ADAM: And that's
when we found out
exactly what I am.

06:06.148 --> 06:07.628
Schizophrenia.

06:07.671 --> 06:09.194
A chronic mental disorder

06:09.238 --> 06:11.893
in which a person
loses touch with reality.

06:11.936 --> 06:14.983
Allowing for visual
and auditory hallucinations.

06:15.026 --> 06:17.507
Paranoia. Delusions.

06:17.551 --> 06:21.424
Hence the chemistry
class extravaganza.

06:21.468 --> 06:24.384
A cornucopia of shit,
basically.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.777
Never goes away, never normal.

06:28.605 --> 06:29.650
The end.

06:32.609 --> 06:34.481
First, they expelled me
from school.

06:39.573 --> 06:43.707
Hey, um, are you still goin'
to Sarah's party next weekend?

06:44.752 --> 06:46.101
Todd's burn was so bad

06:46.144 --> 06:48.320
they had to take skin grafts
from his ass.

06:48.364 --> 06:50.453
Where's your straitjacket,
freak?

06:50.497 --> 06:51.541
ADAM: Now, he hates me.

06:51.585 --> 06:52.890
Hey, come on, guys,
go to class.

06:52.934 --> 06:53.978
BOY: Freak.

06:54.022 --> 06:55.023
ADAM: They all do.

06:57.678 --> 06:59.593
Then Paul hid all the knives.

07:03.161 --> 07:05.163
PAUL: I'm just gonna say this,

07:05.207 --> 07:06.904
but maybe we should send him
some place that knows

07:06.948 --> 07:08.297
how to take care of him.

07:09.951 --> 07:10.952
Professionally.

07:13.694 --> 07:16.218
Just tell me when to start
cracking skulls, kid.

07:17.785 --> 07:20.048
Deep breaths, Adam.

07:20.091 --> 07:21.397
They mean well.

07:23.051 --> 07:25.575
Looks like the neighborhood momsare training for the 10K.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.098
Wanna check it out?

07:27.142 --> 07:30.232
ADAM: Once they showed up,
they never went away.

07:30.275 --> 07:33.409
Like a bunch
of inescapable roommates.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.802
There's Rebecca.

07:34.845 --> 07:38.153
She's sort of Dalai Lama
meets Coachella.

07:39.154 --> 07:40.547
Always zen.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.984
Honestly, I don't mind her
that much.

07:43.027 --> 07:46.378
Then there's The Bodyguard,
which is self-explanatory.

07:46.422 --> 07:48.468
He's temperamental but loyal.

07:48.511 --> 07:50.992
You always gotta watch
your back.

07:51.035 --> 07:53.037
And lastly, there's Joaquin.

07:53.081 --> 07:56.519
He's like the horny best friend from a '90s teen movie

07:56.563 --> 07:57.825
following you around,

07:57.868 --> 07:59.870
saying all
of your unfiltered thoughts.

07:59.914 --> 08:01.524
I know.

08:01.568 --> 08:04.048
It's a lot. [CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

08:04.092 --> 08:05.920
That's where you come in,

08:05.963 --> 08:09.010
now that my mom is
on this hopeless quest
for a cure.

08:09.053 --> 08:11.186
Just like all
the other delusional moms

08:11.229 --> 08:12.622
we've met along the way.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.406
Sitting in
the same waiting rooms.

08:14.450 --> 08:17.192
Putting their faith
in the same doctors.

08:17.235 --> 08:19.716
Quietly begging
for the same thing.

08:20.761 --> 08:22.240
"Cure my kid."

08:26.897 --> 08:31.772
Abilify. Risperdal.
Clozapine. Stelazine.

08:31.815 --> 08:34.557
Name a drug cocktail
and I've tried it.

08:34.601 --> 08:35.950
Any changes at all?

08:36.994 --> 08:39.301
[GRUNTING]

08:43.392 --> 08:44.393
No.

08:45.829 --> 08:49.006
Yet, somehow,
my mom hasn't given up hope.

08:50.486 --> 08:52.444
That makes one of us. I guess.

09:04.631 --> 09:06.284
So, there you have it.

09:07.372 --> 09:09.549
The whole woeful story.

09:09.592 --> 09:11.333
Take it or leave it.

09:11.376 --> 09:12.769
Or maybe just leave it.

09:12.813 --> 09:15.119
'Cause let's be honest,
the only reason we're here

09:15.163 --> 09:18.862
is because my mom's persistence
is inescapable.

09:18.906 --> 09:20.690
And I'm not trying
to take a giant shit

09:20.734 --> 09:22.910
on your life's work or anything,

09:22.953 --> 09:27.915
but I'm part of an elite clubthey call "treatment-resistant."

09:27.958 --> 09:30.221
Which means,
we're probably not gonna have

09:30.265 --> 09:34.356
our own
"It's not your fault" moment
from Good Will Hunting.

09:36.053 --> 09:38.012
So, why don't you
quietly reject me

09:38.055 --> 09:40.144
from this experimental trial

09:40.188 --> 09:42.582
and save us both
the disappointment?

09:45.323 --> 09:46.368
Cool?

09:53.375 --> 09:55.116
BETH: Okay, sweetheart,
time to go.

09:59.511 --> 10:02.776
I told you, I'm not gonna be
someone's guinea pig.

10:02.819 --> 10:04.908
We don't know what'll happen
to me if I take that stuff.

10:04.952 --> 10:06.562
You might start feelin' better.

10:06.606 --> 10:09.260
You just might start spending
a little more time out of bed.

10:09.304 --> 10:10.871
That's what could happen.

10:10.914 --> 10:13.134
Okay, but what if I lose
all my hair?

10:13.830 --> 10:15.223
What if I go blind?

10:15.266 --> 10:16.398
What if it's poisoned?

10:16.441 --> 10:18.356
Honey, who would want
to poison you?

10:18.400 --> 10:21.403
-[KNOCKS ON DOOR]
-We ready?

10:21.446 --> 10:22.578
BETH: Okay, we'll be right down.

10:26.800 --> 10:28.236
Come on.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.238
I have a really good feeling
about this one.

10:31.543 --> 10:32.936
Don't do us dirty, bro.

10:34.590 --> 10:35.722
Can I just take it later?

10:36.418 --> 10:37.811
Fine.

10:37.854 --> 10:38.942
Get dressed.

10:40.727 --> 10:43.338
We have got to go to Brazil.

10:46.167 --> 10:48.212
This looks like
it could be nice.

10:52.739 --> 10:55.045
-[STUDENTS CHATTERING]
-[SCHOOL BELL RINGING]

10:56.960 --> 10:58.962
But I'm not even Catholic.

10:59.006 --> 11:02.400
Catholics are more
about attendance anyway.

11:02.444 --> 11:05.055
It's nice to finally meet you,
Mr. Petrazelli.

11:05.099 --> 11:06.883
[CHUCKLES] You, too.

11:06.927 --> 11:08.624
[WHISPERS] Take it off.

11:08.668 --> 11:11.279
I'm glad you could all make
the drive out here.

11:12.236 --> 11:13.542
Yeah, well, the only person

11:13.585 --> 11:15.544
that can't reject you
is Jesus, right?

11:18.678 --> 11:20.070
[SISTER CATHERINE CHUCKLES]

11:20.114 --> 11:23.291
I think what he means
to say is we are

11:23.334 --> 11:25.510
very appreciative
that you're considering Adam

11:25.554 --> 11:27.077
in the middle
of the school year.

11:27.121 --> 11:28.557
Our Lord embraces all children,

11:28.600 --> 11:30.907
even those with challenges.

11:32.517 --> 11:33.954
We make it a point...
[CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY]

11:33.997 --> 11:35.651
Come on, kid.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.522
Let me take care of her for ya.

11:37.566 --> 11:39.220
She's gonna be
nothing but trouble.

11:39.263 --> 11:41.744
SISTER CATHERINE: We want
to give them the tools...

11:41.788 --> 11:42.745
Suit yourself.

11:46.575 --> 11:47.576
Oh, wow.

11:48.577 --> 11:49.926
Is something wrong?

11:49.970 --> 11:51.406
ADAM: No.

11:51.449 --> 11:52.973
Just wow. Ah.

11:53.756 --> 11:56.106
Quite the display.

11:56.150 --> 12:00.067
Yes, Saint Agatha's is home
to the best and the brightest.

12:00.110 --> 12:01.808
Not just in the school district,

12:01.851 --> 12:04.680
but in all of the county.

12:04.724 --> 12:06.682
And the buck doesn't stop there.
[SIGHS]

12:06.726 --> 12:08.510
Moral and spiritual integrity

12:08.553 --> 12:11.861
are also
of paramount importance.

12:11.905 --> 12:14.559
As you know, Adam's admission

12:14.603 --> 12:17.127
to sucha distinguished academic culture

12:17.171 --> 12:18.825
would be conditional.

12:18.868 --> 12:20.783
These expectations extend to him

12:20.827 --> 12:23.394
regardless of
his medical issues.

12:23.438 --> 12:27.137
That won't be a problem.
Right? Yeah?

12:27.181 --> 12:29.183
Yeah, right.

12:29.226 --> 12:31.272
I'm ready to excel
on all fronts.

12:32.577 --> 12:34.971
It says here...

12:35.015 --> 12:37.757
that Adam has begun
a recent medical trial

12:37.800 --> 12:39.976
to help treat his condition.

12:40.803 --> 12:42.718
Yes, he... he just started.

12:43.545 --> 12:44.851
And how are you feeling?

12:49.159 --> 12:50.770
Uh... [CLICKS TONGUE]

12:50.813 --> 12:51.945
All fired up.

12:52.684 --> 12:53.773
[SHATTERING]

12:55.426 --> 12:56.688
Well,

12:58.429 --> 13:00.823
we can accept Adam.

13:00.867 --> 13:02.607
On the condition
that he maintain

13:02.651 --> 13:04.827
a three-point-five GPA.

13:04.871 --> 13:09.484
And score above a 90%
on the yearly benchmark exam.

13:09.527 --> 13:12.008
Lastly, we would need
monthly updates regarding

13:12.052 --> 13:14.663
his psychiatric treatment,
of course.

13:14.706 --> 13:16.056
That won't be a problem.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.927
Thank you so much.

13:17.971 --> 13:21.061
You'll, uh,
practice discretion, right?

13:21.104 --> 13:25.500
We had an issue with bullying
at his last school.

13:25.543 --> 13:27.415
SISTER CATHERINE:
Perhaps that would be
for the best.

13:27.458 --> 13:29.156
No need to alarm anyone.

13:29.199 --> 13:30.592
PAUL: Okay, thank you.

13:30.635 --> 13:32.028
Adam.

13:32.072 --> 13:33.073
Adam?

13:36.990 --> 13:38.818
I need to go use the restroom.

13:42.909 --> 13:43.953
Just a second.

13:45.912 --> 13:46.869
Hey,

13:47.957 --> 13:49.219
what's wrong?

13:50.177 --> 13:51.787
Don't you see him judging me?

13:52.570 --> 13:53.615
Who, Paul?

13:53.658 --> 13:54.877
Yeah.

13:54.921 --> 13:55.965
He cares about you.

13:56.009 --> 13:58.794
He just doesn't communicate
like us.

13:59.360 --> 14:00.622
Really?

14:00.665 --> 14:02.102
You call this communicating?

14:03.059 --> 14:04.626
Look,

14:04.669 --> 14:05.801
you're going to feel better

14:05.845 --> 14:07.716
once you start taking
the medication.

14:07.759 --> 14:08.804
[SCOFFS] Subtle topic change...

14:08.848 --> 14:10.762
No, you heard her.

14:10.806 --> 14:12.677
You have gotta get serious
about this trial

14:12.721 --> 14:14.505
and about doing well
here, otherwise...

14:15.115 --> 14:16.420
Otherwise what?

14:16.464 --> 14:17.900
No diploma.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.597
No culinary school in the fall.

14:20.772 --> 14:22.731
This is your last chance, Adam.

14:22.774 --> 14:24.472
Sweetie, we can treat this.

14:25.516 --> 14:26.909
You remember
what the doctor said

14:26.953 --> 14:28.302
that just because
you're a person

14:28.345 --> 14:30.608
who's dealing with this illness
doesn't mean...

14:30.652 --> 14:32.175
I'm not the illness itself.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.352
It's hard not to feel like that

14:35.396 --> 14:37.050
when everyone
treats you like one.

14:38.790 --> 14:40.053
I'll be right back.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.459
[URINATING]

14:57.635 --> 14:59.550
[CHUCKLES]

14:59.594 --> 15:01.944
Moral and spiritual integrity,
my ass.

15:01.988 --> 15:03.337
MAYA: How hard is it
for you to meet me

15:03.380 --> 15:04.773
in the bathroom like
we talked about?

15:04.816 --> 15:06.122
Not outside,
never in the hallway.

15:06.166 --> 15:07.384
In, it's a simple concept.

15:07.428 --> 15:08.516
TED: Okay. Get off my nuts,
all right?

15:08.559 --> 15:09.604
We're in the bathroom now...

15:09.647 --> 15:10.648
-MAYA: Cash.
-TED: Yeah.

15:15.001 --> 15:17.177
MAYA: You're short 40,
this isn't charity work.

15:17.220 --> 15:18.526
TED: Okay, I'll get you
the rest next month.

15:18.569 --> 15:20.310
MAYA: No, you still owe me
30 from last month.

15:20.354 --> 15:21.659
[TOILET FLUSHING]

15:23.923 --> 15:25.489
MAYA: Is he with you?

15:25.533 --> 15:26.577
TED: Nope.

15:30.190 --> 15:32.670
You know this wing
is closed for Mass, right?

15:32.714 --> 15:35.978
Her energy is so strong.

15:36.022 --> 15:37.719
I bet she's a Sagittarius.

15:37.762 --> 15:39.503
Are you mute or something?

15:39.547 --> 15:42.332
Scratch that,
definitely a Scorpio.

15:42.376 --> 15:43.638
Not mute.

15:44.204 --> 15:45.683
Um, just new.

15:45.727 --> 15:46.858
Tomorrow's my first day,

15:46.902 --> 15:49.165
I didn't realize
this wing was closed.

15:49.209 --> 15:51.428
Don't get too excited
down there.

15:51.951 --> 15:53.343
Ew.

15:53.387 --> 15:54.997
You didn't see us, okay?

15:55.693 --> 15:57.043
See who?

15:59.915 --> 16:01.482
Us.

16:01.525 --> 16:03.571
-MAYA: I need it by next week.
-I'm gonna sew you a cape...

16:03.614 --> 16:05.225
-MAYA: Shut up.
-...because you're my hero.

16:05.268 --> 16:06.966
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

16:32.904 --> 16:34.732
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

16:37.431 --> 16:39.868
Who are you trying to fool?

16:39.911 --> 16:42.653
[VOICES WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

16:42.697 --> 16:44.351
You'll never make it here.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.155
Yeah.

17:07.156 --> 17:09.593
Um, okay,
I'll see you guys later.

17:13.597 --> 17:15.860
Okay, this is it.
Send out the vibe.

17:15.904 --> 17:18.341
Be cool. Be confident.
Less like you, more like me.

17:18.385 --> 17:20.082
Keep this prasiolite
in your pocket.

17:20.126 --> 17:21.605
It'll boost your confidence.

17:24.652 --> 17:25.653
What is that?

17:27.089 --> 17:28.438
It's my lunch.

17:28.482 --> 17:30.440
Who brings their own sushi
to school?

17:30.484 --> 17:33.052
Beautiful, she's setting you up
for playful banter.

17:34.053 --> 17:35.880
Beats the dog food
they serve here.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.754
The food here
isn't that terrible.

17:39.797 --> 17:42.757
For the tuition, they should be
serving farm-to-table.

17:42.800 --> 17:45.412
So, what, are you some kind
of food snob or something?

17:45.455 --> 17:47.631
Tell her you have
a big palate.

17:47.675 --> 17:50.504
I have a big palate.

17:50.547 --> 17:52.506
-[REBECCA HUMMING]
-Okay.

17:53.507 --> 17:56.249
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

17:56.292 --> 17:59.295
-Hey, right here.
-ADAM: Yeah.

17:59.339 --> 18:01.776
-Hi. Yeah.
-Hi.

18:01.819 --> 18:03.691
You're kind of weird.

18:03.734 --> 18:06.085
No offense,
but are you special needs?

18:06.128 --> 18:07.956
-[GRUNTS]
-[SHOUTS] No!

18:09.175 --> 18:11.090
Just a question, man.

18:11.133 --> 18:13.135
Jeez, didn't mean to get you
all triggered.

18:13.179 --> 18:15.355
I mean, uh, no, I'm not.

18:15.398 --> 18:17.792
I have
this chronic headache syndrome.

18:17.835 --> 18:20.142
So it makes me
blurry sometimes.

18:20.186 --> 18:21.926
Have you ever got
a brain scan for that?

18:21.970 --> 18:23.102
No, why would I?

18:23.145 --> 18:24.886
Well, several malignant tumors

18:24.929 --> 18:27.018
mimic the symptoms
of the common headache.

18:27.062 --> 18:30.631
Acoustic Neuroma,
CNS lymphoma, Meningioma.

18:31.371 --> 18:32.937
Just saying.

18:32.981 --> 18:35.505
I'm pretty sure
they're just headaches.
[CHUCKLES]

18:36.463 --> 18:37.768
I'm Maya.

18:38.421 --> 18:40.162
I'm Adam.

18:40.206 --> 18:43.513
I came over here
to intimidate you into silence

18:43.557 --> 18:45.950
but something tells me
you're pretty harmless.

18:47.256 --> 18:50.085
Are you the school's
drug dealer or something?

18:50.129 --> 18:53.219
You're looking at Saint Agatha'sprojected valedictorian.

18:54.045 --> 18:55.917
Show a little respect.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.353
What's with
all the cloak-and-dagger

18:57.397 --> 18:58.876
in the boys' bathroom?

18:58.920 --> 19:00.400
Just a side hustle.

19:00.443 --> 19:02.010
I'm the kind of person

19:02.053 --> 19:05.100
who knows how to get things
done around here for a price.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.754
Homework, essays.

19:07.494 --> 19:08.843
So you're like

19:08.886 --> 19:11.106
the Bernie Madoff
of academic fraud?

19:11.150 --> 19:13.630
[INHALES SHARPLY]
Sure, only I don't get caught.

19:13.674 --> 19:14.892
[CHUCKLES]

19:18.113 --> 19:19.810
Why are you dressed
for a snowstorm?

19:19.854 --> 19:21.029
It's like 80 outside.

19:22.900 --> 19:24.641
I run cold.

19:24.685 --> 19:26.687
Well, you better hope
they don't catch you
out of your uniform.

19:26.730 --> 19:29.472
Hey, guys. Um, would you like
to sign up for prom tickets?

19:29.516 --> 19:31.692
This year's theme
is Starry Night.

19:31.735 --> 19:33.911
A magical night under His stars.

19:33.955 --> 19:35.783
I think she's talking to you.

19:35.826 --> 19:37.480
I choose to not affiliate myself

19:37.524 --> 19:39.439
with patriarchal norms
like prom.

19:40.744 --> 19:42.964
Um... Thank you.

19:51.364 --> 19:53.931
Hmm. Not bad.

19:53.975 --> 19:57.108
Anyway, uh,
if you need anything,

19:57.152 --> 19:58.458
if you know what I mean,
let me know.

20:04.333 --> 20:06.335
Hey, um, are you guys coming?

20:07.423 --> 20:08.903
Well, no, I don't...

20:08.946 --> 20:11.210
They didn't say the timebut I was just gonna head there.

20:17.520 --> 20:18.913
Bad idea, kid.

20:20.480 --> 20:21.872
Sure.

20:21.916 --> 20:24.223
Good luck getting laid
with jaundice and diarrhea.

20:24.701 --> 20:25.659
MAYA: Yeah.

20:33.928 --> 20:35.886
[ALTER EGOS GROANING]

20:37.714 --> 20:40.587
ADAM: Updates?
I made a new friend. Sort of.

20:40.630 --> 20:42.458
That felt like a win for Adam.[CHUCKLES]

20:42.502 --> 20:45.113
Don't get many of those
when your entire waking life

20:45.156 --> 20:47.507
is an Escape Room with no exit.

20:47.550 --> 20:50.292
Meanwhile,
Paul still tiptoes around me

20:50.336 --> 20:51.946
like I'm going to kill him
in his sleep.

20:53.034 --> 20:54.557
As if being mentally ill

20:54.601 --> 20:56.820
automatically makes
you Jeffrey Dahmer.

20:58.431 --> 20:59.519
What are these?

21:00.607 --> 21:03.871
Um, uh, one less utensil
we have to wash.

21:06.439 --> 21:07.788
Just thought
we'd give 'em a try.

21:08.615 --> 21:10.356
I don't know what's weirder,

21:10.399 --> 21:12.314
seeing things
that aren't actually there,

21:12.358 --> 21:14.098
or sitting across
from a grown man

21:14.142 --> 21:15.709
who is suddenly afraid of me.

21:15.752 --> 21:16.971
So, Adam,

21:18.364 --> 21:21.845
did you learn
something new today?

21:21.889 --> 21:25.936
ADAM: But that's his problem.
Not mine.

21:25.980 --> 21:28.199
I learned that Saint Agatha's

21:28.243 --> 21:31.725
was named after a woman
who refused a man's advances

21:31.768 --> 21:34.554
and subsequently had
her breasts hacked off

21:34.597 --> 21:35.903
as penance.

21:39.254 --> 21:40.342
Wow.

21:43.563 --> 21:45.782
I think Paul was referring
to your coursework.

21:47.001 --> 21:48.002
It was fine.

21:48.872 --> 21:50.265
Not much to say.

21:52.920 --> 21:54.269
Just give it time.

21:55.444 --> 21:56.663
It's a good school.

21:57.664 --> 21:58.926
Okay.

22:11.112 --> 22:12.200
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam...

22:13.201 --> 22:14.376
Adam.

22:15.725 --> 22:18.032
You're ruining
your mother's life, Adam.

22:18.902 --> 22:20.469
You're not the son she wanted.

22:21.688 --> 22:24.168
This is why your father left.

22:24.212 --> 22:27.215
He knew something
was wrong with you.

22:27.258 --> 22:29.391
And soon, everyone
at your new school

22:29.435 --> 22:31.567
will know the truth.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.830
That's when they'll
finally get rid of you.

22:34.744 --> 22:35.745
Gone.

22:36.703 --> 22:37.704
Nothing.

22:38.835 --> 22:41.969
When that voice comes
to visit me,

22:42.012 --> 22:44.928
it's like
I'm having a nightmare

22:44.972 --> 22:46.060
while I'm awake.

22:47.235 --> 22:49.368
I try to close my eyes

22:49.411 --> 22:51.674
and let my mind go blank.

22:51.718 --> 22:53.284
Like you told me to.

22:54.329 --> 22:55.330
But

22:56.810 --> 22:57.941
that doesn't work.

23:01.641 --> 23:02.859
I'm proud of you.

23:03.294 --> 23:04.774
Thanks.

23:04.818 --> 23:07.255
And I maintain that this drug
won't work, either.

23:07.298 --> 23:09.213
Proud of you, honey.

23:09.257 --> 23:12.695
But I was secretly hoping
you'd prove me wrong.

23:12.739 --> 23:13.827
[DOOR CLOSES]

23:15.785 --> 23:16.786
TEACHER: Good.

23:17.961 --> 23:19.223
Very good, Marlene.

23:22.966 --> 23:24.577
BETH: Adam, this is not good.

23:24.620 --> 23:25.926
We have to fix this.

23:25.969 --> 23:28.450
[SIGHS] I'm not trying
to fail math.

23:28.494 --> 23:29.930
I know that.

23:29.973 --> 23:32.541
Okay, but you can't get
kicked out your second week.

23:32.585 --> 23:34.021
This is your life
we're talking about.

23:34.064 --> 23:36.284
Well, I know,

23:36.327 --> 23:37.938
but you're not in my head
with me.

23:41.811 --> 23:43.596
Okay, let's get back
on the same team.

23:45.293 --> 23:46.555
Find your center.

23:47.251 --> 23:48.514
Take a breath.

23:48.557 --> 23:49.689
[INHALES DEEPLY]

23:50.254 --> 23:51.734
Yeah, okay.

23:51.778 --> 23:53.257
Same team.

23:53.301 --> 23:55.216
Maybe Paul could help,
he's a numbers guy.

23:58.785 --> 24:00.743
[CHUCKLING] No, that's...

24:00.787 --> 24:02.266
That's gonna be
a hard pass from me.

24:02.310 --> 24:03.572
BETH: Well, just think
about it, okay?

24:05.095 --> 24:06.270
Okay.

24:07.663 --> 24:09.273
[ENGINE STARTS]

24:10.710 --> 24:11.754
I'll find a tutor.

24:14.540 --> 24:16.019
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

24:17.107 --> 24:18.587
Hey.

24:18.631 --> 24:20.502
Why did you sign your name
in the note?

24:20.546 --> 24:23.897
I was literally looking at you
when you handed it to me.

24:23.940 --> 24:26.856
Kids around here really
have a way with words, huh?

24:26.900 --> 24:28.467
Don't let the academic
achievements fool you.

24:28.510 --> 24:32.471
Everything you need to knowabout Saint Agatha's is in here.

24:32.514 --> 24:34.037
So this is
like the underbelly?

24:34.081 --> 24:36.300
Yeah, and it needs
to stay that way.

24:36.344 --> 24:37.780
If we're gonna do
business together,

24:37.824 --> 24:40.174
you can't be passing notes
in front of Sister Catherine.

24:40.217 --> 24:42.045
Well, that's the thing.

24:42.089 --> 24:44.787
I don't need you to go
all Madoff on me. [CHUCKLES]

24:45.745 --> 24:48.008
I need a tutor.

24:48.051 --> 24:50.532
Yeah, no. I don't do
that kind of bitch work.

24:50.576 --> 24:52.882
Try the student center.

24:52.926 --> 24:54.928
That kid the other day,
he owed you money, right?

25:00.673 --> 25:03.458
You'd be surprised how many
of these rich assholes

25:03.502 --> 25:05.068
don't keep up
their end of the bargain.

25:05.112 --> 25:06.940
[CHUCKLES]

25:06.983 --> 25:09.333
So, do you want to
keep chasing rich assholes

25:09.377 --> 25:10.509
or do you want to get paid?

25:12.380 --> 25:15.383
My mom is willing to pay
for a tutor

25:15.426 --> 25:17.037
and she really wants me
to do well.

25:19.561 --> 25:21.215
200 a week. Three sessions.

25:21.258 --> 25:23.086
All weekdays, one weekend
out of the month.

25:23.609 --> 25:24.653
Jesus.

25:26.176 --> 25:27.874
-Are you serious?
-You get what you pay for.

25:30.050 --> 25:32.182
-How about 100 a week?
-200.

25:32.226 --> 25:34.228
-150?
-Two or I walk. Yes or no?

25:36.752 --> 25:39.625
After I won the
Newton Young Genius Award

25:39.668 --> 25:41.888
from the National Honor Society
in seventh grade,

25:41.931 --> 25:44.499
I got a full ride scholarship
to Saint Agatha's

25:44.543 --> 25:46.762
where I've been the reigning
student body president

25:46.806 --> 25:48.547
since my freshman year

25:48.590 --> 25:51.593
in addition to being captain
of several clubs.

25:51.637 --> 25:53.247
Yearbook, Science, French,

25:53.290 --> 25:56.424
Model United Nations,
to name a few.

25:56.467 --> 25:58.382
But those are just for fun.

25:58.426 --> 25:59.949
My primary focus is academics

25:59.993 --> 26:02.082
as I've received
an early acceptance
to Duke this fall.

26:04.606 --> 26:06.565
Wow. [HESITATES]

26:06.608 --> 26:08.697
Wow, very impressive, Maya.

26:08.741 --> 26:10.220
The upright Lovers card!

26:10.264 --> 26:12.527
Love, union,
mutual attraction...

26:12.571 --> 26:14.616
MAYA: When I do something,
I do it all the way.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.705
Middle ground or halfway

26:16.749 --> 26:19.621
aren't concepts I subscribe to.

26:19.665 --> 26:21.362
So, I will do everything
in my power

26:21.405 --> 26:23.146
to make sure that your boy
doesn't fall behind.

26:23.190 --> 26:24.800
-She's good.
-She is good.

26:24.844 --> 26:26.193
You don't work with adults,
do you?

26:26.236 --> 26:27.237
Um... [CHUCKLES]

26:28.151 --> 26:30.545
You're very impressive, Maya.

26:30.589 --> 26:34.418
Um, but $200 a week
is too much.

26:34.462 --> 26:37.378
Would you accept 75?

26:37.421 --> 26:39.249
Yeah, yeah, that's fine.

26:39.946 --> 26:40.947
Really?

26:42.035 --> 26:43.079
Great!

26:45.168 --> 26:47.780
Pretty impressive dog
and pony show down there.

26:47.823 --> 26:50.478
Yeah, well, I invented the dog
and pony show.

26:50.521 --> 26:51.784
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

26:59.095 --> 27:02.359
Wow, it's so quiet out here.
You can hear everything.

27:03.360 --> 27:05.536
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYS]

27:05.580 --> 27:06.973
-Uh, totally.
-[MUSIC STOPS]

27:07.016 --> 27:09.584
What's with the cookbooks,
Julia Child?

27:09.628 --> 27:12.543
Oh, um, I'm sort of studying
to be a chef.

27:12.587 --> 27:14.676
Sort of, or are you?

27:15.416 --> 27:16.591
I am.

27:18.071 --> 27:19.246
That's your thing?

27:19.289 --> 27:20.334
That's my thing.

27:20.377 --> 27:21.727
You don't hear that every day.

27:21.770 --> 27:23.511
Yeah.

27:23.554 --> 27:27.646
Wow, The Encyclopedia
of Cinnamonby Alicia Tella.

27:27.689 --> 27:30.692
What she can do with cinnamon
is seriously unreal.

27:31.519 --> 27:34.043
-[CHUCKLES]
-What?

27:34.087 --> 27:35.305
Are you surprised

27:35.349 --> 27:37.220
that I've surpassed
your level of nerdiness?

27:37.264 --> 27:39.570
Please, you're talking
to the captain
of the Robotics club.

27:39.614 --> 27:41.834
Oh, well...

27:41.877 --> 27:43.749
I can literally make
the final dish

27:43.792 --> 27:46.621
-served on the Titanic.
-Oh.

27:46.665 --> 27:48.536
You wanna go there?
All right.

27:48.579 --> 27:50.016
For my eighth grade
science fair,

27:50.059 --> 27:51.931
I built a functioning replica
of the Mars rover

27:52.714 --> 27:53.715
out of soda cans.

27:53.759 --> 27:55.674
Well, for my 16th birthday,

27:55.717 --> 27:57.458
I went to a cheese seminar
in Oregon.

27:58.981 --> 28:01.505
Last summer, I won
the Google Science
Talent Search.

28:01.549 --> 28:03.507
You know who hand-picked
my project?

28:03.551 --> 28:04.683
Neil deGrasse Tyson.

28:04.726 --> 28:06.902
-No.
-Come at me.

28:06.946 --> 28:08.991
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

28:09.035 --> 28:10.689
All right, I got nothing.

28:12.168 --> 28:14.562
What? Don't look at me.
Look at her!

28:15.781 --> 28:17.913
You have a problem
with eye contact.

28:17.957 --> 28:20.699
Do you always say exactly
what comes into your mind?

28:20.742 --> 28:24.485
I mean, I could have
a degenerative eye disease
or something.

28:24.528 --> 28:26.182
Yeah, well, it's best to say

28:26.226 --> 28:28.358
exactly what you mean
or nothing at all.

28:28.402 --> 28:30.578
Unrelenting honesty, you know?

28:30.621 --> 28:32.188
That's useful.

28:33.233 --> 28:35.844
This is a new recipe
I'm trying.

28:35.888 --> 28:39.195
Did they teach you this
at your Hogwarts
for Artisan Cheeses?

28:39.239 --> 28:40.980
[CHUCKLES] Just try it.

28:41.023 --> 28:43.199
Are you sure
you can handle the truth?

28:43.243 --> 28:44.723
Guess we'll find out.

28:47.508 --> 28:48.901
JOAQUIN: This is it.

28:48.944 --> 28:50.641
Okay, you're
on the five-yard line.

28:55.037 --> 28:56.473
Wow...

28:56.517 --> 28:58.475
Hook, line, sink. He's in!

29:00.782 --> 29:01.740
What's happening?

29:03.916 --> 29:05.047
Told you not to take the pills.

29:05.091 --> 29:06.266
This is good.

29:06.309 --> 29:08.094
-[JOAQUIN GROANING]
-Like, really good.

29:08.137 --> 29:10.096
[CHUCKLES] Yeah, no, I know.

29:10.139 --> 29:12.359
-It's like...
-[JOAQUIN CONTINUES GROANING]

29:12.402 --> 29:13.926
...earthy.

29:13.969 --> 29:15.579
Maybe smoky, even.

29:15.623 --> 29:17.320
-That's the Fontina cheese.
-JOAQUIN: My goodness.

29:17.364 --> 29:18.800
It's my secret weapon.

29:18.844 --> 29:20.193
JOAQUIN: Can you hear me?

29:20.236 --> 29:23.109
All right, to find
the area of the circle, you...

29:23.152 --> 29:24.937
A equals...

29:24.980 --> 29:27.722
-Pi times R.
-...pi times R

29:29.028 --> 29:30.072
squared.

29:30.116 --> 29:32.335
[CHUCKLES] See, I got this.

29:33.032 --> 29:34.207
Yeah, I'm sure.

29:34.250 --> 29:35.948
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

29:35.991 --> 29:38.689
Hey, guys, it's late.

29:38.733 --> 29:41.257
Maya, how did you get here?
I don't see a car outside.

29:41.301 --> 29:42.781
Yeah, I took the bus.

29:42.824 --> 29:44.304
Okay, well,
let me drive you home.

29:44.347 --> 29:47.307
Oh, you don't have to do that,
I can catch the last bus.

29:47.350 --> 29:48.830
At this hour? Not a chance.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.179
I'll meet you downstairs
in 10.

29:54.575 --> 29:56.142
-MAYA: Yeah, this is it.
-BETH: Okay.

29:56.185 --> 29:57.578
MAYA: Thank you
for driving me.

30:02.888 --> 30:05.368
-MAYA: Um...
-BOTH: I'll see you Monday.

30:12.549 --> 30:14.856
ADAM: Look, I know "cure"

30:14.900 --> 30:17.163
is a dangerous word
amongst my people,

30:17.206 --> 30:19.513
so, I won't say
that's what's happening.

30:20.862 --> 30:23.082
Hey. No.

30:23.909 --> 30:25.562
Don't, don't, don't.

30:25.606 --> 30:27.390
Adam, think about this.
Just don't...

30:27.434 --> 30:28.478
Hey!

30:28.522 --> 30:30.829
[SIGHS] You mother...

30:38.010 --> 30:39.489
[CHUCKLES]

30:42.188 --> 30:46.279
But this is the closest
I've felt to normal

30:46.322 --> 30:48.716
in, well, ever.

30:54.374 --> 30:56.376
No projectile diarrhea

30:56.419 --> 30:58.900
or any other punishing
side effects.

30:59.945 --> 31:01.903
Just some muscle twitching.

31:01.947 --> 31:03.209
No big deal.

31:03.252 --> 31:04.775
It's all good.

31:09.606 --> 31:11.086
I hope it lasts.

31:15.482 --> 31:19.268
[ADAM VOCALIZING]

31:27.407 --> 31:30.410
Eggs Benedict
with well-done bacon...

31:30.453 --> 31:31.759
how you like it.

31:33.456 --> 31:34.849
Good morning to you, too.

31:34.893 --> 31:38.461
The hollandaise sauce
has cayenne pepper.

31:38.505 --> 31:39.767
Let me know what you think.

31:44.511 --> 31:45.512
What?

31:46.730 --> 31:47.731
Nothing.

31:48.994 --> 31:50.038
You seem up lately.

31:50.082 --> 31:51.126
Up?

31:51.170 --> 31:53.433
-Happy.
-[CHUCKLES] Oh.

31:54.260 --> 31:55.348
It's a good look.

31:56.349 --> 31:57.872
Yeah, well, you know...

31:57.916 --> 31:59.091
I feel good.

32:01.397 --> 32:02.833
-Okay, have some. Come on.
-Okay.

32:06.272 --> 32:07.273
Wow.

32:13.279 --> 32:14.715
[MOANS]

32:14.758 --> 32:16.064
Honey, it's so good.

32:16.108 --> 32:17.413
-Yeah? Really?
-Mmm-hmm!

32:17.457 --> 32:19.459
-He's back!
-[LAUGHS]

32:20.547 --> 32:22.331
-Okay.
-Mmm!

32:23.158 --> 32:24.551
I'm back.

32:25.552 --> 32:27.249
Hey, what's with
the heating pad,

32:27.293 --> 32:29.077
is Paul hemorrhoidal?

32:29.121 --> 32:31.732
-Is his prostate flarin' up?
-[COUGHING] God.

32:31.775 --> 32:33.038
No, I'm serious.

32:33.081 --> 32:34.343
-I care about that.
-Stop, you're terrible!

32:34.387 --> 32:35.823
I'm not terrible.
I just care about his spine.

32:35.866 --> 32:38.565
Stop. No, I bought it for you.

32:38.608 --> 32:40.697
I thought it might help
with your muscle spasms.

32:42.743 --> 32:45.441
Mmm. Baby, this is so good.

32:48.923 --> 32:50.881
Wait, did you talk
to my psychiatrist?

32:52.100 --> 32:54.973
Now and then.
That's the agreement, right?

32:55.016 --> 32:57.149
I didn't think
you'd be getting transcripts.

32:57.192 --> 32:59.803
I'm your mom.
My job is to help you.

33:03.590 --> 33:06.245
[BELL TOLLING]

33:23.305 --> 33:24.306
Hi.

33:28.484 --> 33:30.486
Hello?

33:30.530 --> 33:32.053
FATHER PATRICK: In the name
of the Father, the Son,

33:32.097 --> 33:33.750
and the Holy Spirit, amen.

33:34.534 --> 33:36.188
It's your turn.

33:36.231 --> 33:37.885
Sorry, I've never done
this before.

33:37.928 --> 33:40.018
I don't even really believe
in God.

33:40.061 --> 33:41.976
I probably shouldn't say that.

33:42.020 --> 33:43.369
FATHER PATRICK:
Don't overthink it.

33:43.412 --> 33:45.936
There are no rules here.
This is your time.

33:45.980 --> 33:47.895
Do people really
just talk about,

33:47.938 --> 33:49.853
you know, how much
they jerk off and stuff?

33:53.509 --> 33:54.902
Well, everybody in this school

33:54.945 --> 33:56.860
is between the ages
of 13 and 18.

33:56.904 --> 33:58.384
So what do you think?

33:58.427 --> 34:01.169
[CHUCKLING] Well,
that's embarrassing
for everyone.

34:01.213 --> 34:02.649
Long as they don't do it
in here.

34:04.738 --> 34:06.783
John 1:9...

34:06.827 --> 34:09.438
"If we confess our sins,
then He is faithful and just

34:09.482 --> 34:12.615
"and He will purify us
of all unrighteousness."

34:14.052 --> 34:16.880
Really? That's your sales pitch?

34:19.666 --> 34:20.884
It usually works.

34:22.799 --> 34:24.758
Well, what if I just sit here?

34:24.801 --> 34:26.760
Then you can search
your soul for guidance

34:26.803 --> 34:29.284
and I'll enjoy the quiet time.

34:31.939 --> 34:34.289
So, everything I say
stays between us?

34:35.508 --> 34:37.684
And God.

34:37.727 --> 34:39.077
But since you don't believe
in God,

34:39.120 --> 34:40.252
then I guess it's just us.

34:41.253 --> 34:44.125
I see this psychiatrist

34:44.169 --> 34:47.128
and apparently,
she tells my mom everything.

34:47.172 --> 34:48.347
And that bothers you?

34:48.390 --> 34:50.610
Yeah.

34:50.653 --> 34:53.526
I mean, you wouldn't want
your mom reading
your diary, right?

34:53.569 --> 34:55.310
[CHUCKLING]

34:55.658 --> 34:56.877
No.

34:56.920 --> 34:58.226
You're right, that's twisted.

34:58.270 --> 35:00.707
I... I don't think

35:00.750 --> 35:02.230
that I should feel like
I have someone

35:02.274 --> 35:03.666
watching over me all the time.

35:03.710 --> 35:06.060
I feel like I should be able
to live my own life.

35:06.104 --> 35:07.148
Right?

35:07.192 --> 35:09.455
Now, that is
a reasonable request.

35:09.498 --> 35:11.152
Because you should have
the space and autonomy

35:11.196 --> 35:13.154
to become the person
you're going to be.

35:13.198 --> 35:14.155
Right.

35:14.982 --> 35:16.026
Thank you.

35:16.070 --> 35:17.506
You're welcome.

35:17.550 --> 35:20.988
It's nice to be heard
and not just observed.

35:21.031 --> 35:22.468
It's nice to be listened to.

35:23.121 --> 35:24.252
Yeah.

35:24.296 --> 35:25.906
Okay,
I absolve you of your sins

35:25.949 --> 35:28.822
in the name of the Father,
Son, and Holy Spirit. Amen.

35:28.865 --> 35:30.432
Oh, I didn't confess anything.

35:30.476 --> 35:32.304
Just go with it.

35:32.347 --> 35:35.959
I'll admit, I was ready
to come in here guns blazing

35:36.003 --> 35:37.570
over you telling my mom

35:37.613 --> 35:39.615
everything I say
in our sessions.

35:41.574 --> 35:44.098
But then,
something incredible happened.

35:45.665 --> 35:49.756
For the first time in forever,

35:49.799 --> 35:52.498
I woke up the other morning
to complete silence.

35:53.325 --> 35:55.196
No whispers.

35:55.240 --> 35:56.763
No banter.

35:56.806 --> 35:58.634
No visions.

35:58.678 --> 36:03.248
Just pure, beautiful,
unfiltered quiet.

36:03.291 --> 36:05.554
It's amazing
what I've been able to do

36:05.598 --> 36:07.208
with all this extrarenal estate in my brain.

36:07.252 --> 36:08.253
Hey!

36:10.820 --> 36:12.909
Oh, you're pleased
with my services.

36:12.953 --> 36:14.563
-Yeah! What do you think?
-Okay.

36:14.607 --> 36:15.999
It's an A-minus.

36:16.043 --> 36:18.263
-Thank you.
-Mmm.

36:18.306 --> 36:20.221
Hey, don't rest on your laurels,

36:20.265 --> 36:22.484
you're not going to get
another make-up exam
if you shit the bed again.

36:22.528 --> 36:24.921
Right, and that's why I think
we should hang out later.

36:25.748 --> 36:26.749
Hang out?

36:28.577 --> 36:29.709
I mean, study.

36:35.280 --> 36:37.630
MAYA: We could've just studied
in the library.

36:37.673 --> 36:41.111
ADAM: Yeah, well, the library
doesn't serve lobster frittata.

36:41.155 --> 36:42.765
MAYA: You're so weird.

36:43.723 --> 36:45.420
You know, when I first met you,

36:45.464 --> 36:48.989
I thought maybe
he's just awkward
and unsocialized,

36:50.295 --> 36:52.122
but that's not it,
there's something else.

36:52.732 --> 36:53.907
Oh.

36:54.908 --> 36:57.519
Cool. [CHUCKLING] Thanks.

36:57.563 --> 37:00.261
I don't know
what to say to that.

37:01.741 --> 37:03.221
I'm just me.

37:03.264 --> 37:04.744
I'll crack you, Petrazelli.

37:06.441 --> 37:09.009
Hey, let me ask you
a question.

37:09.052 --> 37:12.882
Why does the valedictorian
risk it all for a side hustle?

37:15.711 --> 37:17.757
I like helping people.
Big deal.

37:17.800 --> 37:19.193
[CHUCKLES]

37:20.281 --> 37:22.327
Maybe I'll be the one
to crack you.

37:26.809 --> 37:30.030
Why don't you tell me
about the restaurant
you're taking me to?

37:30.073 --> 37:32.162
[SIGHS] Well, basically,

37:33.947 --> 37:35.253
it's my dream kitchen.

37:35.296 --> 37:39.257
I've studied the menu
for years

37:40.345 --> 37:42.216
and nobody invents like they do.

37:44.174 --> 37:46.176
It's the kind of place
I'd like to work at one day.

37:46.220 --> 37:48.527
Maybe even own, we'll see.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.311
Oh, right, when cheese camp
finally pays off?

37:50.355 --> 37:54.272
Hey, you laugh, but cheese camp
was a spiritual experience.

37:54.315 --> 37:57.318
And the kitchen
is just my place.

37:57.362 --> 38:00.321
When I'm cooking,it's like everything disappears.

38:01.583 --> 38:03.759
And...

38:03.803 --> 38:06.458
I get to be exactly
who I want to be.

38:07.285 --> 38:08.721
I'm in control.

38:10.418 --> 38:11.854
I respect that.

38:13.378 --> 38:15.380
You have to choose
exactly who you wanna be.

38:16.250 --> 38:17.338
Life's too short.

38:25.346 --> 38:26.434
CHEF 1: Got the sirloin.

38:26.478 --> 38:28.480
CHEF 2: Salads are ready.

38:28.523 --> 38:30.090
WAITRESS: Chef wants to see you.

38:30.133 --> 38:32.048
CHEF: Beef tenderloin fillets
are up.

38:32.092 --> 38:33.180
WAITER: Yeah.

38:33.223 --> 38:34.616
WAITRESS: Whole calamari.

38:35.835 --> 38:37.489
CHEF 1:
Is the chocolate sauce ready?

38:37.532 --> 38:38.881
[IMPERCEPTIBLE CONVERSATION]

38:38.925 --> 38:41.493
CHEF 2: That was
two duck breasts for 83.

38:41.536 --> 38:42.711
TODD: All right, guys,

38:42.755 --> 38:44.191
so I got my parents' car
for the night

38:44.234 --> 38:46.933
so whenever you guys are trying
to head out, we can.

38:46.976 --> 38:48.021
I'm trying to head out
as soon...

38:48.064 --> 38:50.240
BOY 1: Hey, yo, check it out.

38:50.284 --> 38:52.721
-Yo, look who it is.
-TODD: Oh, man!

38:52.765 --> 38:54.070
[LAUGHING] I feel like

38:54.114 --> 38:55.463
-such an idiot because...
-What?

38:55.507 --> 38:56.769
I made fun of you
so hard before,

38:56.812 --> 38:58.292
and now, I don't know.

38:58.336 --> 39:00.381
I thought your cheese was betterthan the cheese we had.

39:00.425 --> 39:01.904
-ADAM: Oh, really?
-Look who it is!

39:01.948 --> 39:03.950
-ADAM: That's crazy.
-Hey, straitjacket.

39:03.993 --> 39:05.081
MAYA: That's actually
a good testament to you.

39:05.125 --> 39:06.169
Adam!

39:06.213 --> 39:07.388
BOY 2: Adam!

39:08.607 --> 39:10.391
Hey! Come on, man.

39:10.435 --> 39:12.045
-BOY 3: Yo, get him, dude.
-You know it's us.

39:12.088 --> 39:13.525
TODD: You don't have to mess
with him. Come on, don't...

39:13.568 --> 39:15.396
-BOY 3: Oh, yeah!
-[BOYS EXCLAIMING]

39:15.440 --> 39:17.616
-BOY 2: Got him.
-[BOYS LAUGHING]

39:17.659 --> 39:19.226
BOY 4: Look at his face.

39:19.269 --> 39:20.706
-Hey! You need...
-BOY 3: Loser.

39:20.749 --> 39:22.055
...to apologize, asshole.

39:22.098 --> 39:23.970
-BOY 3: Who're you
callin' an asshole?
-Wow!

39:24.013 --> 39:27.669
Your handler is actually
pretty hot, straitjacket.

39:27.713 --> 39:29.454
-BOY 3: Yes, she is.
-Look, trust me though,

39:29.497 --> 39:31.107
you don't wanna hang out
with this psycho, okay?

39:31.151 --> 39:32.326
-Don't touch me.
-[BOYS EXCLAIMING]

39:32.370 --> 39:33.414
BOY 3: Back up, chick!

39:33.458 --> 39:34.807
-BOY 2: Dude!
-TODD: Both of you, man!

39:34.850 --> 39:37.026
-Hey!
-[BOYS EXCLAIMING]

39:37.070 --> 39:40.943
Hey! Hey! Stop! Stop!
Let it go, all right?

39:41.553 --> 39:42.945
BOY 3: Losers!

39:44.991 --> 39:46.340
What the fuck?

39:46.384 --> 39:47.689
-ADAM: It's okay. It's okay.
-Who was that?

39:47.733 --> 39:48.777
ADAM: I don't know.

39:48.821 --> 39:49.909
-MAYA: Adam, who...
-I don't know.

39:54.870 --> 39:56.481
Hey, I'm sorry about that.

39:57.873 --> 40:00.659
Do you wanna tell me
what that was about?

40:00.702 --> 40:02.487
Um, there's nothing really
to tell.

40:05.098 --> 40:07.840
You know,
I was thinking, isn't it...

40:09.058 --> 40:10.625
Isn't it a little weird

40:10.669 --> 40:13.454
that you left your high school
in the middle of senior year

40:13.498 --> 40:16.152
to go to a Catholic school
outside of your district?

40:16.892 --> 40:17.893
Yeah. Um...

40:20.461 --> 40:21.897
It was a... [SIGHS]

40:21.941 --> 40:23.333
It was a fight.

40:25.335 --> 40:28.426
I got into a fight
with one of those guys.

40:28.469 --> 40:29.514
You were fighting?

40:29.557 --> 40:31.429
Yeah, and it was really bad

40:31.472 --> 40:33.300
so I tried to put it behind me.

40:35.563 --> 40:36.999
That's all you're gonna give me.

40:38.348 --> 40:40.394
MAN: [WHISPERING]
Don't let them take you there.

40:40.438 --> 40:42.788
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
No, I wanna stay here.

40:42.831 --> 40:45.312
I wanna stay right here
on this surface. Mmm-hmm.

40:45.355 --> 40:48.271
[WHISPERING]
Don't let them take you there.

40:48.315 --> 40:51.318
[SHUDDERING]
No. I won't go. I won't go.

40:53.538 --> 40:55.148
Don't let them take you.

40:55.191 --> 40:56.584
It's not good there.

40:57.542 --> 40:58.847
Don't, don't, don't.

41:07.465 --> 41:10.119
Ted, thanks for coming early
for once.

41:15.385 --> 41:16.952
Ted, my office. Now.

41:19.868 --> 41:21.827
Maya, you stay here.

41:23.219 --> 41:24.351
[DOOR OPENS]

41:27.397 --> 41:28.442
[DOOR CLOSES]

41:30.966 --> 41:32.794
How long has this been
going on?

41:33.578 --> 41:35.144
Sister Catherine, I'm...

41:35.188 --> 41:36.842
[VOICE SHAKING]
I'm sorry, I...

41:36.885 --> 41:38.626
How long?

41:38.670 --> 41:41.455
Just a couple months.
Not long.

41:41.499 --> 41:42.630
Seems you and I need to have

41:42.674 --> 41:44.719
a long conversation
about your future.

41:47.809 --> 41:49.898
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

41:49.942 --> 41:53.423
Okay, everyone, bring your eyes
to the board, please.

41:53.467 --> 41:57.993
The state Benchmark Exam
is in just two weeks.

41:58.037 --> 42:00.300
Here's your essay question.

42:00.343 --> 42:03.303
Recount a time
when you faced failure.

42:03.346 --> 42:05.479
How did it affect you

42:05.523 --> 42:09.483
and what did you learn
from the experience?

42:09.527 --> 42:14.575
As you know, no outlines
or scratch paper is allowed.

42:14.619 --> 42:18.710
But please, start thinking
about what you will write.

42:18.753 --> 42:20.363
[BELL RINGING]

42:22.452 --> 42:25.891
All right, everyone,
see you tomorrow.

42:25.934 --> 42:27.545
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

42:32.288 --> 42:33.507
Hey.

42:33.551 --> 42:35.422
-ADAM: Hey. Hey.
-Hey. Hey.

42:35.465 --> 42:37.076
Are we still good for tonight?

42:37.119 --> 42:41.428
MAYA: Um... I have, uh, a...

42:41.471 --> 42:43.822
a club thing after school.
Can I just...

42:43.865 --> 42:45.084
I'll text you later, okay?

42:45.127 --> 42:46.172
Sure.

42:46.999 --> 42:48.174
Come hungry.

42:51.873 --> 42:53.179
ADAM: She never showed up.

42:55.398 --> 42:58.532
And now that
my hallucinations are M.I.A,

42:59.315 --> 43:02.623
everything is so quiet.

43:04.407 --> 43:05.408
Too quiet.

43:08.150 --> 43:09.456
FATHER PATRICK:
In the name of the Father,

43:09.499 --> 43:10.936
the Son,
and the Holy Spirit, amen.

43:10.979 --> 43:12.024
ADAM: Yeah, it's me.

43:13.112 --> 43:14.200
Hello, me.

43:15.157 --> 43:17.116
ADAM: Um...

43:17.159 --> 43:18.639
I need some guidance.

43:19.727 --> 43:22.077
[BREATHES DEEPLY]
Spiritual guidance?

43:22.121 --> 43:24.819
Uh, not really.
It's about a girl.

43:26.125 --> 43:27.343
Okay.

43:27.387 --> 43:29.955
Well, we've been hanging out
for a while

43:29.998 --> 43:31.652
and it was going great,

43:31.696 --> 43:33.741
and then she randomly
stopped talking to me.

43:34.873 --> 43:36.962
I believe the kids
call that ghosting.

43:37.005 --> 43:38.050
Yeah, whatever.

43:38.093 --> 43:40.095
I'm just worried
that maybe she found

43:40.139 --> 43:42.010
some things out about me,

43:42.054 --> 43:44.186
like the psychiatrist
I was telling you about,

43:44.230 --> 43:46.711
which I can't imagine
is the sexiest thing
in the world.

43:47.625 --> 43:48.887
What do you think?

43:48.930 --> 43:51.541
-Have you tried praying on it?
-[CHUCKLES]

43:51.585 --> 43:54.632
No. No offense, but I need
some real life advice.

43:55.241 --> 43:56.677
Timothy 1:7...

43:56.721 --> 43:59.811
"God does not give us
the spirit of cowardice,

43:59.854 --> 44:02.901
"but rather the spirit
of power and of love."

44:02.944 --> 44:05.686
Okay, okay, but is there
anything else that you've got?

44:05.730 --> 44:07.732
Listen, I don't know
the details of your life,

44:07.775 --> 44:10.865
but from where I'm sitting,
you seem quite all right.

44:10.909 --> 44:12.258
You're a little squirrely,
maybe.

44:12.301 --> 44:15.130
-Squirrely?
-Squirrely. Yeah.

44:15.174 --> 44:16.828
And the truth is,
the older you get,

44:16.871 --> 44:20.483
the more difficult it is
to stay sane.

44:20.527 --> 44:22.137
And it's gonna take real work.

44:24.313 --> 44:27.316
Or maybe that's what makes you
more mature than others.

44:27.360 --> 44:29.405
And I hear that girls like
that sort of thing.

44:29.449 --> 44:31.930
So you're saying
I should confront her?

44:31.973 --> 44:33.845
I should tell her how I feel?

44:33.888 --> 44:35.107
Your words, not mine.

44:35.150 --> 44:37.283
[CHUCKLES]

44:37.326 --> 44:40.416
Non-committal
till the bitter end. Thank you.

44:40.460 --> 44:41.548
Go in peace.

44:50.557 --> 44:52.820
Excuse me,
I'm lookin' for Maya.

44:52.864 --> 44:55.344
Oh, there's no one here
by that name.

44:58.391 --> 44:59.740
Are you sure about that?

44:59.784 --> 45:02.743
[CHUCKLES] Yeah. I'm sure.

45:05.877 --> 45:08.880
Do you know a Maya Arnaz?

45:08.923 --> 45:11.883
Mmm-mmm.The only Arnaz I know is the guywho works on my roof.

45:11.926 --> 45:13.275
Manuel Arnaz?

45:14.581 --> 45:15.625
Oh!

45:16.583 --> 45:18.237
Everything okay?

45:18.280 --> 45:19.325
Yeah.

45:21.240 --> 45:22.502
Do you know
where I could find him?

45:50.791 --> 45:51.879
MANUEL: I'm comin'.

45:57.363 --> 45:59.321
-Yeah, what can I do for you?
-[TV PLAYING]

45:59.365 --> 46:01.454
Uh, I'm looking for Maya.

46:02.194 --> 46:03.195
Okay.

46:03.717 --> 46:06.502
I'm Adam.

46:06.546 --> 46:08.983
We're supposed to study tonight.Is she home?

46:09.027 --> 46:11.681
No, she doesn't get off work
for another half an hour.

46:11.725 --> 46:13.205
But, uh, you can come in
and wait if you like.

46:13.248 --> 46:15.033
No, that's okay.
But thank you.

46:15.076 --> 46:16.948
No, no, come on in.
Don't be shy.

46:16.991 --> 46:18.123
Okay.

46:18.166 --> 46:19.428
Are you
from one of those clubs?

46:19.472 --> 46:21.300
I can't keep track
of them anymore.

46:22.127 --> 46:23.389
[TV CONTINUES PLAYING]

46:23.432 --> 46:24.477
Sorry about the mess.

46:24.520 --> 46:25.695
Oh, no. Don't be.

46:25.739 --> 46:27.436
I've been on these crutches
for months.

46:27.480 --> 46:29.482
This is Ricky and Danny.

46:29.525 --> 46:30.962
Boys, uh, this is...

46:31.005 --> 46:32.877
-Adam.
-Say hi to Adam.

46:32.920 --> 46:35.444
-Hey, guys.
-BOTH: Hey.

46:35.488 --> 46:37.620
Don't worry about them,
they're shy.

46:37.664 --> 46:39.622
Not like their sister,
but I'm sure you know that.

46:39.666 --> 46:41.537
-[CHUCKLES]
-Right.

46:41.581 --> 46:43.539
Can I get you something
to drink? Something to eat?

46:43.583 --> 46:45.803
Oh, I'm... I'm good.

46:46.934 --> 46:48.240
Sure?

46:48.283 --> 46:50.416
We've got, uh, TV dinners

46:51.591 --> 46:52.810
and TV dinners.

46:52.853 --> 46:54.812
Yeah, no, I'm all good.
Thanks.

46:54.855 --> 46:56.291
BOTH: We want TV dinners.

46:56.335 --> 46:58.641
Oh, they have spoken.
[CHUCKLES]

46:58.685 --> 47:00.556
-[PHONE RINGING]
-Oh, shoot!

47:00.600 --> 47:01.775
ADAM: Hey,
I can put those in for you.

47:01.819 --> 47:02.994
Are you sure?

47:03.037 --> 47:04.125
-Yeah. No, no, no problem.
-You don't mind?

47:04.169 --> 47:05.083
Oh, thanks!
That'd be a great help.

47:05.126 --> 47:06.301
ADAM: Yeah.

47:06.345 --> 47:07.868
Two minutes each, I think.
Check the box.

47:07.912 --> 47:09.652
[PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

47:09.696 --> 47:12.830
MANUEL: Arnaz Roofing.
Hi, Mrs. Jenkins.

47:14.266 --> 47:16.877
Oh, you're having trouble
with your gutters again?

47:16.921 --> 47:20.620
Yeah, well, look, I'm still
on medical leave. So...

47:20.663 --> 47:22.840
Yeah, I can refer you
to Galloway.

47:22.883 --> 47:24.885
Yeah, he's a great guy.
Mmm-hmm.

47:24.929 --> 47:26.365
Yeah, Bill will take care
of you.

47:27.845 --> 47:29.281
-[DOOR OPENS]
-ADAM: Yeah, yeah,

47:29.324 --> 47:31.674
so the secret is to marinate
the chicken for flavor.

47:31.718 --> 47:33.198
-MANUEL: Oh, okay.
-ADAM: Olive oil,

47:33.241 --> 47:35.504
chopped garlic, salt, pepper...

47:35.548 --> 47:38.116
And then you brush
a little butter
over the top there.

47:38.159 --> 47:39.552
-MANUEL: That's it?
-That's it.

47:40.945 --> 47:42.903
-Hey.
-DANNY: I can eat all of it.

47:42.947 --> 47:44.557
-[MANUEL CHUCKLING]
-Here. You good?

47:44.600 --> 47:45.863
Oh, look at this.

47:45.906 --> 47:47.168
-DANNY: Thanks, Adam.
-RICKY: Thanks, Adam.

47:47.212 --> 47:49.040
-ADAM: Yeah, no problem.
-Come on in.

47:49.083 --> 47:50.911
It's a little spread
your friend whipped up here.

47:50.955 --> 47:52.826
-MAYA: Hey.
-DANNY: Hey.

47:52.870 --> 47:54.306
It's awesome.

47:56.395 --> 47:58.223
[WHISPERING] Hey, um,

47:58.266 --> 47:59.789
what are you doing here?

47:59.833 --> 48:02.923
Oh, we had a study session,
remember?

48:02.967 --> 48:04.055
RICKY: The chicken tastes nice.

48:04.098 --> 48:05.143
Right.

48:05.186 --> 48:06.274
This is amazing.

48:06.318 --> 48:08.015
[CHUCKLING] Yeah? Good.

48:08.059 --> 48:09.277
MANUEL: 'Cause you never know
what's hiding

48:09.321 --> 48:11.236
-in your fridge I guess.
-[ADAM CHUCKLES]

48:11.279 --> 48:12.933
How'd you get so good
in the kitchen?

48:12.977 --> 48:16.067
Oh, I've been cooking
my whole life.

48:16.110 --> 48:18.852
You know, one day, hopefully,
I'll own my own restaurant.

48:18.896 --> 48:19.940
MANUEL: Wow.

48:19.984 --> 48:21.159
You had to go to school
for that?

48:21.202 --> 48:22.290
DANNY: Okay, fine.

48:22.334 --> 48:25.076
Yeah, Dad,
it's culinary art school.

48:25.119 --> 48:28.296
Oh. Yeah. Right, right.

48:28.340 --> 48:30.211
Well, for you to spend
your whole life working,

48:30.255 --> 48:32.735
might as well make it
something you enjoy, right?

48:32.779 --> 48:34.650
I always try to tell Maya that.

48:34.694 --> 48:37.349
You know,
she'll be the first Arnaz
to get her college degree.

48:37.392 --> 48:39.742
Her mother would've been
so proud.

48:39.786 --> 48:41.353
She was a smart lady, too,
you know.

48:41.396 --> 48:42.571
Dad...

48:42.615 --> 48:44.182
[CHUCKLING] What?

48:44.225 --> 48:46.010
Let me brag about my daughter.

48:47.533 --> 48:49.796
Well, one day,
my little girl here,

48:49.839 --> 48:51.798
she's gonna pick me up
in a Porsche.

48:51.841 --> 48:53.582
She's been saying that
since she was 10.

48:53.626 --> 48:54.627
Sorry, excuse me.

49:07.335 --> 49:09.337
Why did you do this?

49:09.381 --> 49:11.687
I didn't mean
to upset you, honestly.

49:11.731 --> 49:13.733
I went to the other house
and the lady just sent me here.

49:13.776 --> 49:15.517
So you just decided
to make yourself at home

49:15.561 --> 49:16.866
by cooking dinner?

49:16.910 --> 49:18.303
I thought it'd be
a nice thing to do.

49:18.346 --> 49:19.739
You did it because it was
a nice thing to do

49:19.782 --> 49:21.001
or because you felt sorry
for us?

49:21.045 --> 49:24.439
I wouldn't... No.
I don't feel sorry for you.

49:25.397 --> 49:27.790
Are you satisfied then?

49:27.834 --> 49:29.009
Good job! You found
our tiny little house,

49:29.053 --> 49:30.228
in a rundown neighborhood

49:30.271 --> 49:32.012
so you could cook us
poor people dinner.

49:33.144 --> 49:34.188
You're a real saint.

49:42.327 --> 49:43.545
I'm sorry.

49:46.070 --> 49:47.985
Sister Catherine caught me.

49:49.551 --> 49:52.337
Side hustle's dead,

49:52.380 --> 49:54.426
and I'm not making enough money
tutoring you.

49:56.471 --> 50:00.127
This restaurant pays me
under the table.

50:01.041 --> 50:02.042
And it's good.

50:03.565 --> 50:05.350
My family depends on me.

50:10.572 --> 50:13.053
You know, the only reason
I'm getting a second chance

50:13.097 --> 50:16.100
is 'cause I'm valedictorian.

50:16.143 --> 50:19.016
You have no idea how hard
I worked to get here.

50:22.367 --> 50:24.021
I can't lose it all now.

50:25.065 --> 50:26.023
No.

50:27.328 --> 50:29.243
You're not gonna lose anything.

50:30.984 --> 50:32.290
You're like a robot.

50:33.334 --> 50:35.162
Immune to human error.

50:36.772 --> 50:40.080
And my schedule is wide open,
you know.

50:40.124 --> 50:43.083
So we can meet whenever.

50:45.999 --> 50:47.522
There are other tutors
out there.

50:47.566 --> 50:48.828
You know that, right?

50:48.871 --> 50:51.744
None like you.

50:51.787 --> 50:54.486
I like knowin' I get to see you
three times a week.

51:06.498 --> 51:09.240
[ADAM CHUCKLES]

51:09.283 --> 51:11.198
A Brief History of Time.

51:11.242 --> 51:13.113
Pale Blue Dot.

51:13.157 --> 51:15.942
And then... Would this be
your favorite movie?

51:15.985 --> 51:18.901
Do I, uh, detect a hint
of smugness in your voice?

51:18.945 --> 51:20.990
[CHUCKLING] Not at all.

51:21.034 --> 51:24.385
I actually
really love this one.

51:24.429 --> 51:26.474
'Cause it's a classic.
You know that, right?

51:27.562 --> 51:29.303
It's a cinematic masterpiece.

51:31.958 --> 51:33.438
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

51:41.489 --> 51:42.708
Thank you for cooking.

51:46.929 --> 51:47.930
Sure.

51:50.846 --> 51:54.154
Don't forget to show your workwhen doing the sine ratio, okay?

51:54.198 --> 51:55.721
Okay.

51:55.764 --> 51:57.114
Otherwise...

51:58.767 --> 52:02.031
Looks good. Great work!

52:02.075 --> 52:05.470
Watch out. I may be coming
for your academic throne.

52:05.513 --> 52:07.341
Never. Um...

52:08.690 --> 52:10.823
But I do have
a surprise for you,

52:10.866 --> 52:12.868
since you've been
killing it lately.

52:16.045 --> 52:18.570
ADAM: Whoa. [CHUCKLES]

52:18.613 --> 52:21.442
You can thank my dad,
he fixed the roof last winter

52:21.486 --> 52:23.227
so he's pretty tight
with the owner.

52:24.184 --> 52:26.143
Oh, man... [CHUCKLES]

52:31.583 --> 52:33.933
Are these the MAC MH-90s?

52:33.976 --> 52:35.935
[LAUGHING] I don't know.

52:39.330 --> 52:40.940
This grill's insane.

52:43.203 --> 52:46.163
I don't know about you,
but I'm pretty hungry.

52:51.777 --> 52:55.389
So, you don't follow a recipe?

52:55.433 --> 52:58.392
Everyone thinks cooking is
about following instructions,

52:58.436 --> 53:00.612
but it's the opposite.

53:00.655 --> 53:03.397
Your palate will tell you
exactly what the dish wants.

53:07.271 --> 53:09.795
So, we need to talk
about benchmark exams
next week.

53:09.838 --> 53:11.144
Right.

53:11.188 --> 53:13.320
Why is everyone so obsessed
with those here?

53:13.364 --> 53:14.669
Are they really hard?

53:14.713 --> 53:16.758
I mean, no,
they're not so much hard

53:16.802 --> 53:19.544
as they are a means
to keep the school funded.

53:19.587 --> 53:21.415
Plus, the top three
are read at graduation

53:21.459 --> 53:23.374
so, you know, St. Agatha kids,

53:23.417 --> 53:24.897
they live for that crap.

53:24.940 --> 53:26.072
[PAN SIZZLING]

53:26.115 --> 53:27.856
MAYA: Um...

53:27.900 --> 53:30.642
I was, um, thinking

53:32.600 --> 53:33.862
that maybe you could write

53:33.906 --> 53:36.430
about what happened
at your old school...

53:36.474 --> 53:39.128
I mean, if you see it
as a failure...

53:40.217 --> 53:42.131
-I see what you're doing.
-What?

53:42.175 --> 53:44.917
[CHUCKLES] You're digging
for more answers.

53:46.048 --> 53:48.181
MAYA: I'm digging
for more answers?

53:48.225 --> 53:50.618
You showed up at my house,
you basically stalked me.

53:50.662 --> 53:51.793
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

53:52.664 --> 53:53.926
Yeah, I guess.

53:56.842 --> 53:58.670
[CHUCKLING] Okay, okay.

53:59.279 --> 54:00.715
Okay. Um...

54:02.413 --> 54:05.372
I guess, in the beginning,

54:06.895 --> 54:08.984
I tried not to see it
as a failure,

54:09.811 --> 54:11.596
but it's hard not to.

54:13.815 --> 54:15.252
After the fight,

54:16.427 --> 54:19.517
people immediately
looked at me differently

54:20.692 --> 54:22.563
like they were afraid of me.

54:25.871 --> 54:29.744
No matter what I did,
I couldn't get them to see me

54:29.788 --> 54:31.224
as they did before.

54:34.358 --> 54:35.663
But I let that happen.

54:37.361 --> 54:39.754
I, I became a bystander
in my own life.

54:43.497 --> 54:45.891
I guess that's what felt like
the real failure.

54:53.507 --> 54:55.901
[ADAM EXHALES DEEPLY]

54:56.380 --> 54:57.381
Hey.

55:03.212 --> 55:04.257
[SIZZLING]

55:07.608 --> 55:09.828
[COUGHS, CLEARS THROAT]

55:09.871 --> 55:11.090
-[COUGHS]
-What?

55:11.133 --> 55:12.178
[CLEARS THROAT] Mm-mm.

55:12.221 --> 55:13.875
It's good. It's very good.

55:13.919 --> 55:15.050
[CONTINUES COUGHING]

55:15.094 --> 55:17.705
What happened
to unrelenting honesty?

55:20.578 --> 55:22.057
I'm... I'm sorry, I...

55:22.101 --> 55:23.972
I know you worked
really hard on that.

55:24.016 --> 55:26.323
What's wrong with it?

55:26.366 --> 55:27.976
No, I think you just added

55:28.020 --> 55:29.804
a little bit too much spice
or something.

55:29.848 --> 55:30.849
[CLEARING THROAT]

55:36.681 --> 55:38.335
It tastes fine to me.

55:41.816 --> 55:42.904
SISTER CATHERINE:
All of your belongings

55:42.948 --> 55:44.166
should be under your desk,

55:44.210 --> 55:45.603
out of sight.

55:45.646 --> 55:47.213
No exceptions.

55:47.256 --> 55:49.650
The only materials
I should see

55:49.694 --> 55:52.697
are the Scantron,
a number two pencil,

55:52.740 --> 55:55.439
your calculator,
and the test booklet.

55:55.482 --> 55:57.179
[ECHOING AND DISTORTING]
Absolutely nothing else

55:57.223 --> 55:58.616
should be visible.

55:58.659 --> 56:01.749
You will have 60 minutes
for the mathematics portion

56:01.793 --> 56:05.187
and 90 minutes
for the essay question.

56:05.231 --> 56:06.711
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Begin.

56:06.754 --> 56:07.886
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

56:18.462 --> 56:20.507
BETH: Are you not that hungry?

56:20.551 --> 56:22.988
ADAM: Oh, no, I, um...

56:23.989 --> 56:25.077
BETH: It's your favorite.

56:25.120 --> 56:26.252
ADAM: Yeah.

56:26.295 --> 56:27.427
BETH: Paul picked it up
from Vince's.

56:27.471 --> 56:29.429
Yeah. Thanks, Paul.

56:29.473 --> 56:30.952
You're welcome.

56:30.996 --> 56:32.954
[CLEARS THROAT] So, actually,
we have something

56:32.998 --> 56:34.260
we need to talk to you about.

56:34.303 --> 56:35.740
And I just want you to know

56:35.783 --> 56:38.133
that everything
is gonna be okay.

56:39.004 --> 56:40.005
Okay?

56:41.746 --> 56:43.487
Did somebody die?

56:43.530 --> 56:45.402
No, nobody's dying.

56:45.445 --> 56:47.708
No, everybody's okay.
Everybody's alive.

56:52.626 --> 56:54.323
I'm pregnant,

56:55.368 --> 56:56.978
and we're gonna have a baby.

56:59.372 --> 57:01.069
Like a human baby?

57:01.113 --> 57:02.157
[CHUCKLING]

57:02.201 --> 57:03.768
Jeez, I hope so.

57:04.421 --> 57:05.422
[CHUCKLES]

57:08.642 --> 57:11.558
[ECHOING AND DISTORTING] Look,
we didn't plan this at all.

57:13.560 --> 57:14.996
You know?
And we're just getting

57:15.040 --> 57:16.998
our heads around this now.

57:17.042 --> 57:19.087
-Adam?
-[RATTLING]

57:19.131 --> 57:20.872
Adam?

57:20.915 --> 57:22.134
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Adam.

57:22.177 --> 57:23.440
You okay, buddy?

57:24.571 --> 57:25.833
Yeah.

57:27.531 --> 57:29.663
Yeah, congratulations.

57:31.883 --> 57:35.190
Okay, all right,
I'm gonna go to the office,

57:35.234 --> 57:37.628
get ready for tomorrow's work.

57:37.671 --> 57:40.718
[KISSES]
If anybody needs me...

57:42.937 --> 57:45.679
Adam. Look at me.

57:47.812 --> 57:50.989
I promise
nothing is going to change.

57:51.032 --> 57:53.644
What are you talking about?

57:55.167 --> 57:56.951
Everything will.

57:56.995 --> 57:59.954
[ECHOING AND DISTORTING]
No, I mean between you and I.

57:59.998 --> 58:02.043
Look, I know
this isn't the right time.

58:03.828 --> 58:06.308
I'm scared, too,
believe me, but it's also...

58:06.352 --> 58:07.571
ADAM: [IN NORMAL VOICE]
Okay, I was reading

58:07.614 --> 58:09.007
the pamphlet you gave me

58:09.050 --> 58:11.313
about the potential
side effects of this drug.

58:11.357 --> 58:14.621
Dehydration, sweating,
trouble urinating,

58:14.665 --> 58:16.710
vision loss, muscle tension,

58:16.754 --> 58:18.451
loss of taste and hearing,

58:18.495 --> 58:19.583
tremors,

58:19.626 --> 58:21.323
oh, and my personal favorite,

58:21.367 --> 58:23.456
anal leakage.

58:23.500 --> 58:26.285
You can go ahead and cross
most of those off the list.

58:26.328 --> 58:29.331
I can't cook anymore, because
my taste comes and goes.

58:29.375 --> 58:30.637
I can barely piss straight

58:30.681 --> 58:32.987
because my hand
has a mind of its own.

58:34.685 --> 58:36.687
But I swear,

58:36.730 --> 58:38.906
if anything drips
out of my ass,

58:38.950 --> 58:40.517
please just kill me.

58:42.867 --> 58:43.868
Morning.

58:49.047 --> 58:51.571
-Have a good day.
-You, too.

58:51.615 --> 58:52.746
I love you.

59:01.363 --> 59:02.626
Have a good day, hon.

59:19.904 --> 59:21.166
Have a good day, honey.

59:23.472 --> 59:25.039
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

59:25.605 --> 59:26.693
[ADAM SIGHS]

59:29.522 --> 59:31.785
Someone should really keep
an eye on that kid.

59:40.925 --> 59:44.145
[REBECCA CHANTING OM]

59:46.104 --> 59:47.975
Good morning.

59:48.019 --> 59:49.542
Morning, boss.

59:49.586 --> 59:51.936
Yeah, yeah, we missed you.

59:55.374 --> 59:56.549
[GRUNTS]

59:58.029 --> 59:59.030
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1:00:00.597 --> 1:00:04.775
Um, okay, we're starting
at Chapter 5, I think.

1:00:04.818 --> 1:00:06.646
-Five.
-It's page 403.

1:00:06.690 --> 1:00:08.648
-I'm on it.
-403, do you have it?

1:00:08.692 --> 1:00:10.171
-Yeah.
-Okay.

1:00:10.215 --> 1:00:11.651
Um... All right.

1:00:11.695 --> 1:00:14.132
MAYA: [CLEARS THROAT] "Angles
in X-Y coordinate system."

1:00:15.220 --> 1:00:16.917
"Angles formed by rotating ray

1:00:16.961 --> 1:00:18.440
"or a half-line
about its end point,

1:00:18.484 --> 1:00:19.790
"the initial side
of the angle,

1:00:19.833 --> 1:00:22.009
"starting position
of the ray."

1:00:22.053 --> 1:00:25.622
Final position
of the ray rotation,
did you get that?

1:00:25.665 --> 1:00:26.623
[COUGHING]

1:00:28.494 --> 1:00:30.670
[SHARPENING]

1:00:30.714 --> 1:00:31.889
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

1:00:31.932 --> 1:00:34.718
[SOUNDS AMPLIFYING,
DISTORTING]

1:00:34.761 --> 1:00:36.241
Adam.

1:00:39.244 --> 1:00:42.682
You thought you
could get rid of me.

1:00:42.726 --> 1:00:44.075
You feel that?

1:00:45.250 --> 1:00:46.686
I'm still here.

1:00:46.730 --> 1:00:48.819
You don't know that,
you just know.

1:00:48.862 --> 1:00:50.734
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
Don't fight it, Adam.

1:00:51.560 --> 1:00:53.693
Adam.

1:00:53.737 --> 1:00:56.609
Adam.

1:00:56.653 --> 1:00:57.915
Adam!

1:00:57.958 --> 1:01:00.613
You need to go. Now.

1:01:00.657 --> 1:01:02.484
Adam, what do you think?

1:01:03.921 --> 1:01:07.751
Um... Sorry. I'm...
I'm not feeling so good.

1:01:14.148 --> 1:01:17.108
Hey. hey, Adam.
hey, hey, what's wrong?

1:01:18.326 --> 1:01:19.371
What'd I say, huh?

1:01:19.414 --> 1:01:20.981
Get out of here!

1:01:21.025 --> 1:01:23.157
I gotta go. I gotta go.
They're gonna take me,

1:01:23.201 --> 1:01:24.245
-and I gotta go, okay?
-Wait.

1:01:24.289 --> 1:01:25.769
Take you where?
What are you...

1:01:25.812 --> 1:01:26.987
I can't keep her safe, too.

1:01:27.031 --> 1:01:28.728
-Adam.
-Stop!

1:01:30.512 --> 1:01:33.646
Just leave me alone,
and don't follow me.

1:01:35.909 --> 1:01:37.737
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

1:01:44.135 --> 1:01:46.354
[MALE VOICE WHISPERING] Adam.

1:01:46.398 --> 1:01:47.442
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:01:51.795 --> 1:01:54.058
FEMALE VOICE:
Over here.

1:01:54.101 --> 1:01:56.016
[BABY CRY ECHOING]

1:02:09.900 --> 1:02:12.163
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES]

1:02:25.829 --> 1:02:28.309
MALE VOICE: Adam.

1:02:28.353 --> 1:02:29.789
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES]

1:02:35.839 --> 1:02:37.884
[FEMALE VOICE WHISPERING]
She never wanted you.

1:02:37.928 --> 1:02:40.452
She doesn't love you.

1:02:40.495 --> 1:02:42.497
MALE VOICE:
He hates you.

1:02:42.541 --> 1:02:46.327
ADAM'S DARKNESS: This
is the kid she always wanted.

1:02:46.371 --> 1:02:50.331
The one that'll make up
for her biggest mistake.

1:02:50.375 --> 1:02:51.898
You.

1:02:57.556 --> 1:02:58.905
Everything all right?

1:03:00.559 --> 1:03:02.300
Were you watching me?

1:03:02.343 --> 1:03:04.345
No.

1:03:04.389 --> 1:03:05.956
I was just heading to bed.

1:03:07.261 --> 1:03:08.741
Everything okay?

1:03:11.788 --> 1:03:15.008
Sister Catherine called.

1:03:15.052 --> 1:03:17.750
She expressed some concerns
about your behavior this week.

1:03:17.794 --> 1:03:20.622
Having a kid with my mom
doesn't make you my dad.

1:03:20.666 --> 1:03:22.363
Adam, I'm not going anywhere.

1:03:23.016 --> 1:03:25.149
Yeah, clearly.

1:03:28.456 --> 1:03:30.981
ADAM: When I was a freshman,

1:03:31.024 --> 1:03:33.548
there was this girl at
our school who was a junior,

1:03:33.592 --> 1:03:36.813
and she was diagnosed
with terminal bone cancer.

1:03:38.075 --> 1:03:39.554
She was part of
the Make-A-Wish Foundation,

1:03:39.598 --> 1:03:41.818
so before she died,

1:03:41.861 --> 1:03:43.863
they had some boy band
come to our school

1:03:43.907 --> 1:03:47.867
and have lunch with her
as part of her wish.

1:03:47.911 --> 1:03:50.000
It was a really
touching thing.

1:03:50.043 --> 1:03:52.611
It was all people could
talk about for weeks.

1:03:54.308 --> 1:03:55.875
But it got me thinking.

1:03:57.616 --> 1:03:59.357
When you're a cancer kid,

1:04:00.532 --> 1:04:04.057
people can't wait
to flock to your aid,

1:04:04.101 --> 1:04:07.582
and are so eager to
grant any wish you have
before you die.

1:04:10.107 --> 1:04:12.413
But when you have
schizophrenia,

1:04:12.457 --> 1:04:15.329
people can't wait to make you
someone else's problem.

1:04:17.070 --> 1:04:19.986
That's why
we end up on the streets,

1:04:20.030 --> 1:04:21.422
screaming at nothing,

1:04:22.554 --> 1:04:24.034
waiting to die.

1:04:26.993 --> 1:04:29.082
No one wants
to grant our wishes.

1:04:34.827 --> 1:04:35.872
Hey.

1:04:38.570 --> 1:04:40.877
I'm sorry about the other day.

1:04:40.920 --> 1:04:44.184
I just wasn't feeling good.

1:04:44.228 --> 1:04:45.664
-I'm sorry.
-[SIGHS]

1:04:48.667 --> 1:04:51.844
Are you sure
that it's just headaches?

1:04:51.888 --> 1:04:53.541
I'm worried about you.

1:04:53.585 --> 1:04:55.282
Yeah, I'm fine.

1:04:56.849 --> 1:04:58.242
Let me make it up to you.

1:04:59.852 --> 1:05:01.071
Please.

1:05:11.342 --> 1:05:12.386
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1:05:18.871 --> 1:05:21.047
GIRL: She won't let me
go out...

1:05:21.830 --> 1:05:23.354
MAYA: No way.

1:05:23.397 --> 1:05:24.485
[ADAM CHUCKLES]

1:05:24.529 --> 1:05:26.009
Way.

1:05:26.052 --> 1:05:29.186
[MAYA LAUGHING]

1:05:29.229 --> 1:05:30.317
You didn't.

1:05:30.361 --> 1:05:32.406
ADAM: I did.

1:05:32.450 --> 1:05:35.105
MAYA: You know, usually,
this stuff doesn't impress me,

1:05:35.148 --> 1:05:39.674
but, um,
this is... pretty smooth.

1:05:40.719 --> 1:05:42.112
[MOVIE PLAYING]

1:05:48.422 --> 1:05:49.946
JOSIE THROUGH SPEAKERS:
Thank you.

1:05:51.512 --> 1:05:54.951
Um, may I have five minutes
on the clock, please?

1:05:54.994 --> 1:05:56.126
[APPLAUSE IN MOVIE]

1:06:02.306 --> 1:06:03.437
JOAQUIN: Okay, kid.

1:06:03.481 --> 1:06:04.525
We both know
this part of the movie

1:06:04.569 --> 1:06:05.962
is the ultimate panty-dropper.

1:06:06.005 --> 1:06:07.485
Better make your move.

1:06:07.528 --> 1:06:09.008
Hey, just take your time.

1:06:09.443 --> 1:06:10.836
No rush.

1:06:12.403 --> 1:06:15.014
KIRSTEN THROUGH SPEAKERS:
That is so wrong.

1:06:15.058 --> 1:06:16.973
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH SPEAKERS]

1:06:31.944 --> 1:06:32.945
[INHALES SHARPLY]

1:06:38.646 --> 1:06:40.997
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam... Adam.

1:06:41.040 --> 1:06:44.087
Hey, over here.

1:06:44.130 --> 1:06:45.392
Adam.

1:06:45.436 --> 1:06:46.741
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:06:46.785 --> 1:06:48.004
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Adam.

1:06:50.093 --> 1:06:51.746
That's not good.

1:06:55.315 --> 1:06:56.577
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES]

1:07:01.800 --> 1:07:02.844
[FIRE CRACKLES]

1:07:02.888 --> 1:07:03.889
[GASPS]

1:07:06.065 --> 1:07:07.371
[IN SING-SONG VOICE] Finally!

1:07:07.414 --> 1:07:09.460
No way!
What is going on with you?

1:07:09.503 --> 1:07:11.027
Nothing, I'm fine.

1:07:11.070 --> 1:07:12.985
No, you're not fine.

1:07:13.029 --> 1:07:14.117
You don't even look like

1:07:14.160 --> 1:07:15.857
you're on this planet
half the time.

1:07:15.901 --> 1:07:18.251
Adam, look, you can trust her.

1:07:19.600 --> 1:07:22.038
No, you're right.
There is something.

1:07:22.081 --> 1:07:23.865
[SOFTLY] Yeah.

1:07:23.909 --> 1:07:24.997
Yeah, just show her
who you are.

1:07:25.041 --> 1:07:26.390
Tell her about us.

1:07:26.433 --> 1:07:27.608
Don't do that.

1:07:30.872 --> 1:07:33.440
There's been
a lot going on at home.

1:07:33.484 --> 1:07:34.963
Lately.

1:07:35.007 --> 1:07:37.749
I've been feeling
really alone.

1:07:37.792 --> 1:07:40.273
I'm sorry.

1:07:40.317 --> 1:07:43.059
But I don't feel that way
when I'm with you.

1:07:47.846 --> 1:07:49.413
Oh, yeah.

1:07:51.023 --> 1:07:52.285
So...

1:07:54.331 --> 1:07:55.462
I wanted...

1:07:57.160 --> 1:07:59.771
I wanna know if you'd wanna go
to prom with me?

1:08:01.512 --> 1:08:02.687
[EXHALES]

1:08:07.083 --> 1:08:10.303
I know it's an extension of
the patriarchy and everything,

1:08:11.435 --> 1:08:13.132
but would you?

1:08:13.176 --> 1:08:16.483
Only if you tell people
that I asked you.

1:08:17.615 --> 1:08:19.486
-Deal.
-Deal.

1:08:19.530 --> 1:08:20.661
Aw.

1:08:22.185 --> 1:08:23.534
[MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH SPEAKERS]

1:08:38.375 --> 1:08:41.247
 Well, it's been
building up inside of me

1:08:41.291 --> 1:08:44.990
 For, oh
I don't know how long

1:08:46.209 --> 1:08:47.775
 I don't know why

1:08:47.819 --> 1:08:49.212
 But I keep thinking

1:08:49.255 --> 1:08:53.651
 Something's bound to go wrong

1:08:53.694 --> 1:08:57.568
 But she looks in my eyes

1:08:57.611 --> 1:08:59.874
 And makes me realize

1:08:59.918 --> 1:09:01.920
ADAM: My mom
told me something once

1:09:01.963 --> 1:09:04.792
when she first
started dating again.

1:09:04.836 --> 1:09:08.274
You lose your secrets when you let people get too close.

1:09:08.318 --> 1:09:10.015
It can be painful,

1:09:10.058 --> 1:09:11.277
to let someone find you

1:09:11.321 --> 1:09:13.627
in all the dark
and twisty places inside.

1:09:13.671 --> 1:09:16.326
But you have to hope they do,

1:09:16.369 --> 1:09:18.850
because that's the beginning
of everything.

1:09:21.287 --> 1:09:24.725
But letting Maya love me
the way that I am

1:09:24.769 --> 1:09:28.164
would be like letting her
catch a disease.

1:09:28.207 --> 1:09:30.862
She doesn't deserve to
be loved by someone

1:09:30.905 --> 1:09:33.734
who can't see the world
the way it is.

1:09:33.778 --> 1:09:34.779
Right?

1:09:36.607 --> 1:09:38.217
And I'd really like to
keep my secrets

1:09:38.261 --> 1:09:39.653
while I have them.

1:09:47.792 --> 1:09:49.446
You wanna explain these?

1:09:53.319 --> 1:09:54.668
What do you want me to say?

1:09:54.712 --> 1:09:56.583
I want you to say that
you haven't stopped

1:09:56.627 --> 1:09:58.498
taking your medication
behind my back.

1:10:00.108 --> 1:10:02.023
I can't say that.

1:10:03.111 --> 1:10:04.548
Do you have any idea

1:10:04.591 --> 1:10:06.767
how much we have on the line
with this school?

1:10:08.595 --> 1:10:10.336
With your medical expenses?

1:10:11.685 --> 1:10:13.121
What about me?

1:10:14.645 --> 1:10:16.212
What about what I need?

1:10:16.255 --> 1:10:18.692
What are you talking about?
It's all about you.

1:10:18.736 --> 1:10:20.955
It's all about you.
All the time.

1:10:20.999 --> 1:10:22.957
All of this is for you.

1:10:23.001 --> 1:10:24.829
The books, and the articles,

1:10:24.872 --> 1:10:29.225
and the sitting up all night
reading forum after forum.

1:10:29.268 --> 1:10:32.053
Do you think you're
the only one in this house
going through this?

1:10:32.097 --> 1:10:34.926
So that's what they tell you
in those parenting books?

1:10:34.969 --> 1:10:37.015
Oh, my God!

1:10:37.058 --> 1:10:39.844
You know, you are not
the only person in this house

1:10:39.887 --> 1:10:41.715
who is affected by this.

1:10:41.759 --> 1:10:43.195
Do you think that
this is the life

1:10:43.239 --> 1:10:44.718
that I wanted for you?

1:10:44.762 --> 1:10:46.416
For myself?

1:10:46.981 --> 1:10:48.244
Okay.

1:10:48.287 --> 1:10:51.421
I'm sorry for getting
in the way of you,

1:10:51.464 --> 1:10:53.074
and Paul, and the new baby,

1:10:53.118 --> 1:10:55.338
and your perfect new life

1:10:55.381 --> 1:10:59.429
that doesn't include a crazy
stepson who hears voices.

1:11:00.430 --> 1:11:02.475
Stop. Adam.

1:11:02.519 --> 1:11:05.304
[SIGHS] Adam. Stop.

1:11:06.479 --> 1:11:08.873
Listen to me.

1:11:08.916 --> 1:11:12.268
I know that
you must be scared,

1:11:12.311 --> 1:11:14.922
and that it's lonely
in your head,

1:11:14.966 --> 1:11:17.316
and I wish, I wish
I could be in there with you,

1:11:17.360 --> 1:11:20.711
I wish I could ease
that burden, but I can't.

1:11:20.754 --> 1:11:22.843
I'm trying.
I am really trying.

1:11:22.887 --> 1:11:25.019
And I would do anything
for you.

1:11:25.063 --> 1:11:26.934
Just tell me what to do.
Tell me.

1:11:26.978 --> 1:11:28.588
Tell me how to help you.

1:11:35.116 --> 1:11:37.467
There's nothing you can do.

1:11:39.164 --> 1:11:42.689
The pills make me feel like
I wanna die.

1:11:42.733 --> 1:11:46.867
I can't see. I can't think.
And I can't cook.

1:11:47.999 --> 1:11:50.001
And what's the point
if I can't cook?

1:11:50.044 --> 1:11:52.351
Why didn't you share that
with me?

1:11:52.395 --> 1:11:54.135
We're in this together.
We're...

1:11:54.179 --> 1:11:56.224
We're supposed to be
on the same team, remember?

1:11:56.268 --> 1:11:58.923
We're not on the same team.

1:11:58.966 --> 1:12:02.056
And we haven't been
since Paul moved in.

1:12:10.587 --> 1:12:12.110
BETH: I can't do that to him.

1:12:12.153 --> 1:12:13.329
PAUL: Look, I understand that.

1:12:13.372 --> 1:12:16.027
Just listen to me.
We have to do something.

1:12:16.070 --> 1:12:17.333
BETH: I know that, Paul.

1:12:17.376 --> 1:12:18.377
PAUL: It's only a matter
of time before you...

1:12:18.421 --> 1:12:19.813
BETH: I'm doing
everything I can.

1:12:19.857 --> 1:12:21.815
PAUL: Do you see him?
Do you see what's going on?

1:12:21.859 --> 1:12:24.122
BETH: Of course, I see him.
I see everything.

1:12:24.165 --> 1:12:25.471
I'm his mother.

1:12:25.515 --> 1:12:26.864
PAUL: I'm trying
to avert the disaster.

1:12:26.907 --> 1:12:28.866
We ain't taking no damn pills,
you hear me?

1:12:28.909 --> 1:12:30.041
JOAQUIN: You didn't
need those pills.

1:12:30.084 --> 1:12:31.085
BODYGUARD:
We gotta get him outta here.

1:12:31.129 --> 1:12:32.391
Screw the pills!

1:12:32.435 --> 1:12:33.914
-REBECCA: Okay.
-You're awesome,

1:12:33.958 --> 1:12:35.655
and we're here for you.
And we believe in you.

1:12:35.699 --> 1:12:37.527
BODYGUARD: We ain't gonna
let 'em take us out of ya.

1:12:37.570 --> 1:12:39.006
This is our house! Ours!

1:12:39.050 --> 1:12:40.094
JOAQUIN: This bed
is really comfy.

1:12:40.138 --> 1:12:41.139
[VOICES STOP]

1:12:46.057 --> 1:12:47.188
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

1:13:07.426 --> 1:13:09.689
Sorry. You startled me.

1:13:17.393 --> 1:13:19.090
ADAM'S DARKNESS: You're trash.

1:13:21.266 --> 1:13:22.354
What?

1:13:24.965 --> 1:13:26.924
Could you throw away
your trash?

1:13:30.144 --> 1:13:31.276
Sure.

1:13:36.455 --> 1:13:38.239
-[GRUNTING]
-[SHATTERING]

1:13:38.283 --> 1:13:39.632
[GRUNTING CONTINUES]

1:13:49.729 --> 1:13:50.730
You know...

1:13:52.645 --> 1:13:54.995
I was really starting
to look forward

1:13:55.039 --> 1:13:56.997
to our Good Will Hunting
moment.

1:14:00.087 --> 1:14:01.654
TEACHER: When you're finished
with the questions,

1:14:01.698 --> 1:14:02.873
please pass them forward

1:14:02.916 --> 1:14:05.919
and open up your textbooks
to Chapter 18.

1:14:05.963 --> 1:14:07.486
[CHUCKLES]

1:14:07.530 --> 1:14:08.835
[BEEPS]

1:14:08.879 --> 1:14:10.533
SISTER CATHERINE THROUGH PA:
Adam Petrazelli,

1:14:10.576 --> 1:14:13.318
please report to
the Principal's office.

1:14:18.802 --> 1:14:21.195
Adam, please, take a seat.

1:14:27.332 --> 1:14:28.812
-ADAM: Mom, what's going on?
-It's okay.

1:14:28.855 --> 1:14:30.161
It has been brought
to my attention

1:14:30.204 --> 1:14:32.816
that you are no longer taking
your medication.

1:14:34.034 --> 1:14:38.430
Yeah, okay, it...
It made me worse.

1:14:38.474 --> 1:14:40.301
As I said from day one,

1:14:40.345 --> 1:14:43.217
your admission to St. Agatha's
is conditional.

1:14:43.261 --> 1:14:45.219
We can't take any risks.

1:14:45.263 --> 1:14:46.656
What does that mean? Risks?

1:14:46.699 --> 1:14:49.572
They're afraid you're gonna
hurt other students, Adam.

1:14:50.616 --> 1:14:52.009
Are you kicking me out?

1:14:52.052 --> 1:14:53.837
-Suspending you.
-BETH: Temporarily.

1:14:53.880 --> 1:14:56.492
Just... Just until
we figure things out.

1:14:56.535 --> 1:14:59.364
You may finish off the day
to avoid causing a scene.

1:15:01.801 --> 1:15:04.021
It was you.

1:15:04.064 --> 1:15:05.762
I saw you writing
that email to her.

1:15:05.805 --> 1:15:06.937
I know you wanna send me away.

1:15:06.980 --> 1:15:08.591
Adam, you need to calm down.

1:15:08.634 --> 1:15:10.201
No one wants to send you away.

1:15:10.244 --> 1:15:12.725
Yes, he does. And he's a liar.

1:15:14.901 --> 1:15:16.903
This was my last chance.

1:15:19.036 --> 1:15:21.778
I probably
won't get another one.

1:15:21.821 --> 1:15:23.388
Remember, Mom?

1:15:26.957 --> 1:15:27.958
[DOOR SLAMS]

1:15:33.398 --> 1:15:34.399
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1:15:38.490 --> 1:15:40.579
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:15:49.632 --> 1:15:51.677
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES]

1:16:02.079 --> 1:16:03.646
MAYA: Are you surprised?

1:16:05.169 --> 1:16:06.953
What? Why?

1:16:06.997 --> 1:16:08.912
It's... actually nice

1:16:08.955 --> 1:16:11.088
to have some competition
around here for once.

1:16:11.131 --> 1:16:13.569
-What are you talking about?
-[CHUCKLES] Come on. Let's go.

1:16:14.439 --> 1:16:15.658
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1:16:20.837 --> 1:16:22.490
[GIRL EXCLAIMS]

1:16:26.277 --> 1:16:27.974
I'm proud of you, Petrazelli.

1:16:43.381 --> 1:16:45.296
Aren't you supposed
to be in class?

1:16:46.427 --> 1:16:48.429
I didn't feel like it.

1:16:48.473 --> 1:16:50.606
You wanna hop in the box
and talk about it?

1:16:54.348 --> 1:16:56.829
What I'm dealing with
can't be fixed, Father.

1:17:06.839 --> 1:17:08.667
Try me.

1:17:08.711 --> 1:17:11.365
What is even
the purpose of all this?

1:17:12.062 --> 1:17:14.717
Confession?

1:17:14.760 --> 1:17:16.849
You think making people
feel like shit

1:17:16.893 --> 1:17:18.895
somehow brings out
the best in them?

1:17:18.938 --> 1:17:20.679
Cool philosophy.

1:17:20.723 --> 1:17:24.552
"Whoever conceals their sins
does not prosper,

1:17:24.596 --> 1:17:27.294
"but the one that confesses
and renounces them..."

1:17:27.338 --> 1:17:30.254
That's great.

1:17:30.297 --> 1:17:32.343
Another fortune cookie answer.

1:17:34.171 --> 1:17:36.173
You have a list
that you alternate?

1:17:38.828 --> 1:17:40.699
Maybe.

1:17:40.743 --> 1:17:45.486
Being ambiguous
doesn't make you profound.

1:17:47.401 --> 1:17:49.839
It makes you full of shit.

1:17:51.231 --> 1:17:52.276
FATHER PATRICK:
Here's something...

1:17:52.319 --> 1:17:53.364
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
Here's something

1:17:53.407 --> 1:17:54.452
profound for you...

1:17:54.495 --> 1:17:56.280
Why don't you kill yourself?

1:17:59.718 --> 1:18:00.850
What?

1:18:00.893 --> 1:18:02.634
I said, why don't you
excuse yourself?

1:18:02.678 --> 1:18:04.505
Take a day off.
Leave yourself alone.

1:18:04.549 --> 1:18:06.725
That's not what you said.

1:18:12.905 --> 1:18:14.211
This is bullshit.

1:18:14.254 --> 1:18:16.082
Hey, don't talk to your mother
like that!

1:18:16.126 --> 1:18:17.736
Thanks for the parenting
advice, Paul.

1:18:17.780 --> 1:18:19.782
What makes you think you could
go to the prom tonight?

1:18:19.825 --> 1:18:22.306
-You're suspended.
-This is insane!

1:18:22.349 --> 1:18:24.656
Hey, let's just
sit down, okay?

1:18:24.700 --> 1:18:25.875
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:18:25.918 --> 1:18:27.746
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
You're trapped.

1:18:27.790 --> 1:18:30.880
I'm trapped.
This is how it starts.

1:18:30.923 --> 1:18:31.968
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
This is how they do it.

1:18:32.011 --> 1:18:33.665
This is how you do it.

1:18:33.709 --> 1:18:35.319
First, it's the pills.

1:18:35.362 --> 1:18:37.103
Then the pills make me
feel like shit,

1:18:37.147 --> 1:18:38.278
so, I come off of them.

1:18:38.322 --> 1:18:40.672
And that's when Paul
convinces you

1:18:40.716 --> 1:18:41.934
-to send me somewhere.
-[BETH SHUSHING]

1:18:41.978 --> 1:18:43.762
Because nothing else works!

1:18:46.112 --> 1:18:47.766
Nothing else works!

1:18:47.810 --> 1:18:49.725
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Because
nothing was designed to work.

1:18:49.768 --> 1:18:52.423
Nothing was designed to work.
That was the plan!

1:18:52.466 --> 1:18:53.990
And I was right.

1:18:54.033 --> 1:18:55.556
-PAUL: That wasn't the plan.
-I was right the whole time.

1:18:55.600 --> 1:18:56.862
That wasn't the plan, Adam.

1:18:56.906 --> 1:18:58.429
Shut up, Paul!

1:18:58.472 --> 1:19:00.779
-You poisoned my brain.
-BETH: Hey.

1:19:00.823 --> 1:19:02.650
ADAM: You know
he did that, Mom.

1:19:02.694 --> 1:19:04.217
-Can you see that?
-Adam.

1:19:04.261 --> 1:19:06.306
-Mom. Can you see that?
-Come on. Come on.

1:19:06.350 --> 1:19:09.483
BETH: Hey, hey, hey. Hey.
Listen to me.

1:19:09.527 --> 1:19:11.007
Listen to my voice.

1:19:11.050 --> 1:19:13.357
My voice is the only one
that matters right now, okay?

1:19:13.400 --> 1:19:17.970
And I am telling you that
you are my entire world, okay?

1:19:19.015 --> 1:19:20.016
Adam?

1:19:21.626 --> 1:19:23.149
Come on, kid.

1:19:23.193 --> 1:19:25.238
Don't you see it's all
a big bait and switch?

1:19:26.022 --> 1:19:27.937
Adam?

1:19:27.980 --> 1:19:30.374
You better get out of here
before it's too late.

1:19:31.984 --> 1:19:33.116
BETH: Adam.

1:19:34.204 --> 1:19:35.640
I don't believe you.

1:19:41.254 --> 1:19:42.690
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1:20:00.186 --> 1:20:03.363
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
Oh, Adam, Adam, Adam...

1:20:04.582 --> 1:20:05.757
What are you doing?

1:20:05.801 --> 1:20:08.673
No. Please...

1:20:10.544 --> 1:20:13.939
ADAM'S DARKNESS: You're really
gonna go to prom unprepared?

1:20:13.983 --> 1:20:15.985
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:20:17.029 --> 1:20:19.815
[MUFFLED PROM MUSIC PLAYING]

1:20:19.858 --> 1:20:21.468
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING
CONTINUES]

1:20:23.514 --> 1:20:25.733
ADAM'S DARKNESS: That's it.

1:20:25.777 --> 1:20:28.084
How else will you
