1:24:46.037 --> 1:24:47.734
-Adam, Adam, Adam.
-[STRUGGLING]

1:24:47.778 --> 1:24:49.606
Slow down. Slow down.
You're all right. You're okay.

1:24:49.649 --> 1:24:51.216
PARAMEDIC 2: Breathe, breathe.

1:24:59.050 --> 1:25:00.356
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

1:25:12.107 --> 1:25:13.108
Hey.

1:25:14.805 --> 1:25:17.373
What's going on? Where's Maya?

1:25:17.416 --> 1:25:19.114
Is she okay?

1:25:19.157 --> 1:25:21.638
She's, uh...
She's worried about you.

1:25:21.681 --> 1:25:23.161
[SNIFFLES]

1:25:23.205 --> 1:25:24.597
We all are.

1:25:28.862 --> 1:25:30.212
Does she know?

1:25:31.735 --> 1:25:33.606
I told her, honey.

1:25:34.651 --> 1:25:36.696
No, no, no.

1:25:37.741 --> 1:25:38.742
No.

1:25:41.310 --> 1:25:42.441
No.

1:25:43.573 --> 1:25:45.575
What is this?

1:25:45.618 --> 1:25:47.359
-PAUL: Adam.
-What's going on?

1:25:47.403 --> 1:25:48.665
PAUL: That's just
for your own safety.

1:25:48.708 --> 1:25:50.014
-Shut up, Paul. Shut up.
-BETH: Hey. [SHUSHES]

1:25:50.057 --> 1:25:52.016
-It's just temporary.
-Where am I?

1:25:52.059 --> 1:25:54.061
Listen, you were upset,

1:25:54.105 --> 1:25:55.976
and we didn't want you
to hurt yourself.

1:25:56.020 --> 1:25:58.240
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1:25:58.283 --> 1:25:59.806
Okay, when can I go home?

1:25:59.850 --> 1:26:02.113
You have to get better first.

1:26:07.510 --> 1:26:08.989
You wanted to put me here,

1:26:09.033 --> 1:26:11.035
in a place
where they could fix me.

1:26:11.078 --> 1:26:12.471
"Professionally."

1:26:12.515 --> 1:26:13.733
It's not how I meant it, Adam.

1:26:13.777 --> 1:26:15.996
[KNOCKING]

1:26:16.040 --> 1:26:17.041
Hi.

1:26:23.221 --> 1:26:25.745
Can you please make her leave?

1:26:25.789 --> 1:26:27.747
Adam...

1:26:27.791 --> 1:26:30.097
Oh, I'm ready, boss.
All you gotta do

1:26:30.141 --> 1:26:31.490
-is say the word.
-[SHOUTS] Stop!

1:26:31.534 --> 1:26:32.578
Don't... Don't move.

1:26:34.406 --> 1:26:39.585
Adam, listen to me.
She can accept all of you.

1:26:39.629 --> 1:26:41.544
Okay, please,
everyone be quiet.

1:26:44.808 --> 1:26:46.679
This is it.

1:26:46.723 --> 1:26:48.986
This is what it means
to let someone find you

1:26:49.029 --> 1:26:51.118
in all the dark
and twisty places inside.

1:26:51.162 --> 1:26:52.642
Shut up!

1:26:52.685 --> 1:26:54.905
No, this can be the beginning
of everything, remember?

1:26:54.948 --> 1:26:56.820
Shut up! Shut up!

1:27:01.085 --> 1:27:03.305
Are you happy?

1:27:03.348 --> 1:27:05.220
This is who I am.

1:27:06.003 --> 1:27:08.527
It's my big secret, okay?

1:27:08.571 --> 1:27:10.399
No, this isn't who you are.

1:27:10.442 --> 1:27:12.270
Yes, it is!

1:27:12.314 --> 1:27:15.273
I am crazy, and I'm dangerous.

1:27:16.318 --> 1:27:18.320
And I'm...

1:27:18.363 --> 1:27:20.452
I need you to leave.

1:27:20.496 --> 1:27:21.845
No.

1:27:21.888 --> 1:27:25.152
[SHOUTING] Do I look like
I need a fucking tutor?

1:27:27.590 --> 1:27:30.506
Find some other way
to keep the lights on!

1:27:31.376 --> 1:27:32.812
Make her leave.

1:27:32.856 --> 1:27:34.771
-Please. Everyone, get out!
-BETH: Okay.

1:27:37.339 --> 1:27:39.732
Don't touch me.

1:28:03.190 --> 1:28:04.844
This is Seroquel?

1:28:04.888 --> 1:28:06.716
Yeah, I tried that one.

1:28:06.759 --> 1:28:08.979
 You probably think
you're going to Heaven

1:28:10.372 --> 1:28:13.723
 Even though
you put me through hell

1:28:13.766 --> 1:28:17.553
 You're preachy like
you're some kind of reverend

1:28:17.596 --> 1:28:19.990
 I wish you'd turn
the light on yourself

1:28:20.033 --> 1:28:23.602
 You thought
that if you wrecked my car

1:28:23.646 --> 1:28:27.345
 Those flames
would mend your broken heart

1:28:27.389 --> 1:28:31.044
 I know you say
it's all my fault

1:28:31.088 --> 1:28:33.873
 But, darling
if these walls could talk

1:28:35.962 --> 1:28:39.575
 They'd say that you should
put down your weapons

1:28:39.618 --> 1:28:42.317
 Before you go
and start up a war

1:28:43.666 --> 1:28:47.147
 There's no point
in getting upset here

1:28:47.191 --> 1:28:49.541
 You can't tell
what you're fighting for

1:28:49.585 --> 1:28:53.110
 I know you're telling
all your friends

1:28:53.153 --> 1:28:56.983
 Those things
I wish I never said

1:28:57.027 --> 1:29:00.335
 I know you won't
pick up my calls

1:29:00.378 --> 1:29:03.294
 But, darling
if these walls could talk 

1:29:03.338 --> 1:29:05.035
FATHER PATRICK: Good morning.

1:29:08.560 --> 1:29:10.040
You see him, right?

1:29:11.433 --> 1:29:13.478
Yeah, he's real.

1:29:13.522 --> 1:29:15.915
Group session in four minutes.

1:29:15.959 --> 1:29:16.960
Okay.

1:29:19.745 --> 1:29:21.312
What are you doing here?

1:29:21.356 --> 1:29:23.923
FATHER PATRICK: I'm on my way
to the graduation ceremony.

1:29:23.967 --> 1:29:26.186
I just wanted to see
how you were doing.

1:29:26.230 --> 1:29:27.927
ADAM: I've had better days.

1:29:30.103 --> 1:29:32.192
Are you even allowed
to be fraternizing

1:29:32.236 --> 1:29:34.020
with someone like me?

1:29:34.064 --> 1:29:36.022
You know
I got expelled, right?

1:29:36.066 --> 1:29:37.937
FATHER PATRICK: The only
agenda I serve is God's.

1:29:40.244 --> 1:29:42.942
ADAM: Could you tell him
to maybe reconsider his agenda,

1:29:42.986 --> 1:29:45.902
'cause it feels like
I'm getting
the short end of the stick.

1:29:46.598 --> 1:29:48.339
I'll put in a call.

1:29:48.383 --> 1:29:49.514
You mind if I sit?

1:29:51.342 --> 1:29:52.430
Go ahead.

1:30:00.525 --> 1:30:02.135
Well, joking aside,
I want to talk to you

1:30:02.179 --> 1:30:03.615
about the question
you asked me the other day.

1:30:03.659 --> 1:30:05.443
About the point of confession.

1:30:05.487 --> 1:30:06.488
Okay.

1:30:06.531 --> 1:30:07.967
Sometimes,
kids come to see me,

1:30:08.011 --> 1:30:09.491
and they wanna know
what it all means.

1:30:09.534 --> 1:30:11.318
And I usually quote the Bible,

1:30:11.362 --> 1:30:13.146
allowing them
to attach their own meaning.

1:30:14.757 --> 1:30:16.106
Trust me. I know.

1:30:18.848 --> 1:30:20.980
But sometimes,
a kid needs more.

1:30:21.024 --> 1:30:23.548
Actually telling somebody
our sins

1:30:23.592 --> 1:30:26.725
is just an opportunity
to admit that we are flawed.

1:30:26.769 --> 1:30:28.771
You don't think
we know we're flawed?

1:30:28.814 --> 1:30:29.946
FATHER PATRICK:
Everyone's flawed.

1:30:29.989 --> 1:30:32.557
But admitting our flaws,

1:30:32.601 --> 1:30:37.257
that gives us the opportunity
and the strength to face them.

1:30:38.781 --> 1:30:40.739
And that's why we confess.

1:30:45.483 --> 1:30:46.919
I'm sorry
I didn't tell you all this

1:30:46.963 --> 1:30:48.878
before everything happened.

1:30:48.921 --> 1:30:51.489
But I had no idea
what you were up against.

1:30:52.403 --> 1:30:53.926
Sure.

1:30:53.970 --> 1:30:56.451
You want to pray with me
before I go?

1:30:56.494 --> 1:30:58.583
What if I still don't believe
in God?

1:30:59.410 --> 1:31:00.672
Then I will pray.

1:31:00.716 --> 1:31:01.847
But you need to take the time
to think about

1:31:01.891 --> 1:31:03.414
what kind of person
you wanna be.

1:31:03.458 --> 1:31:06.461
At the very least, you need
to believe in yourself.

1:31:12.728 --> 1:31:14.991
Dear Father in heaven,

1:31:15.034 --> 1:31:17.472
please watch over Adam
on his road to recovery.

1:31:21.388 --> 1:31:22.389
[KNOCKING]

1:31:24.087 --> 1:31:25.131
Hi.

1:31:25.175 --> 1:31:26.306
I'm gonna wait downstairs.

1:31:26.350 --> 1:31:27.482
BETH: Okay.

1:31:30.659 --> 1:31:32.574
They said you haven't been
eating much,

1:31:32.617 --> 1:31:35.664
so I thought you might want
something fresh.

1:31:35.707 --> 1:31:37.492
They made me take
all the skewers out.

1:31:37.535 --> 1:31:39.624
It looked a lot better
in the store.

1:31:42.540 --> 1:31:43.541
No, thanks.

1:31:45.412 --> 1:31:47.327
How are you doing?

1:31:47.371 --> 1:31:48.851
How do I look?

1:31:53.551 --> 1:31:54.509
[BETH SIGHS]

1:31:57.033 --> 1:31:58.687
This is temporary.

1:31:58.730 --> 1:32:02.473
No diploma, no culinary school.

1:32:03.953 --> 1:32:05.868
It's over.

1:32:06.521 --> 1:32:07.826
This is my life now.

1:32:07.870 --> 1:32:09.349
That's not true.

1:32:13.310 --> 1:32:15.791
You used to tell me
to see myself

1:32:15.834 --> 1:32:17.967
as a person dealing
with an illness,

1:32:19.795 --> 1:32:22.624
but not become
the illness itself.

1:32:23.494 --> 1:32:26.279
But look at me.

1:32:26.323 --> 1:32:30.240
I am looking at you,
and I see my son.

1:32:31.415 --> 1:32:33.156
Who I love more than anything.

1:32:36.333 --> 1:32:39.031
Come on. You wanna go get
something to eat downstairs?

1:32:39.075 --> 1:32:41.077
No, I'm okay, but thank you.

1:32:59.530 --> 1:33:01.010
See you later.

1:33:01.880 --> 1:33:02.968
ADAM: Okay.

1:33:13.370 --> 1:33:15.590
PAUL: Dear Sister Catherine,

1:33:15.633 --> 1:33:18.636
I met Adam a little
over a year ago.

1:33:18.680 --> 1:33:21.857
I don't have much
experience with kids,

1:33:21.900 --> 1:33:25.077
but knowing Adam has taught me that being a parent

1:33:25.121 --> 1:33:28.254
means becoming
what your children need most.

1:33:28.298 --> 1:33:31.083
Every step of the treatment
has been reported.

1:33:31.127 --> 1:33:33.695
Not because we were
required to do so,

1:33:33.738 --> 1:33:36.436
but because it is in
Adam's best interest

1:33:36.480 --> 1:33:38.177
to have the adults in his life

1:33:38.221 --> 1:33:40.223
be as informed as possible.

1:33:45.010 --> 1:33:47.883
Your threat to
expel him is abusive,

1:33:47.926 --> 1:33:49.711
and we will not tolerate it.

1:33:49.754 --> 1:33:52.278
Right now, my son needs me

1:33:52.322 --> 1:33:56.543
to protect him from
narrow-minded people
motivated by fear.

1:33:56.587 --> 1:34:00.025
I have faith that you will
make a decision

1:34:00.069 --> 1:34:02.985
that reflects the moral
and spiritual integrity

1:34:03.028 --> 1:34:05.161
-St. Agatha's is built upon.
-ADAM: Paul!

1:34:05.204 --> 1:34:07.859
Paul. Paul.

1:34:15.171 --> 1:34:16.520
I'm sorry.

1:34:17.434 --> 1:34:18.565
It's okay.

1:34:19.349 --> 1:34:20.524
It's okay.

1:34:24.789 --> 1:34:27.270
I know you didn't sign up
for this.

1:34:28.140 --> 1:34:29.794
I'm not going anywhere.

1:34:31.404 --> 1:34:33.537
I'm not trying
to replace your dad.

1:34:34.538 --> 1:34:36.888
No, I know.

1:34:36.932 --> 1:34:38.411
But he was an asshole anyway.

1:34:41.197 --> 1:34:43.416
I need you
to take me somewhere.

1:34:43.460 --> 1:34:45.592
What? Where?

1:34:47.116 --> 1:34:48.334
Look, there is no cure,

1:34:48.378 --> 1:34:50.206
and maybe one day,
there will be,

1:34:50.249 --> 1:34:54.210
but right now, I gotta work
this out on my own terms.

1:34:54.253 --> 1:34:56.125
And I can't do that here.

1:34:56.908 --> 1:35:00.172
Please, Mom, be with me

1:35:00.956 --> 1:35:02.218
on the same team.

1:35:03.610 --> 1:35:04.873
Okay.

1:35:05.569 --> 1:35:07.092
Okay.

1:35:07.136 --> 1:35:08.485
-Okay.
-Okay.

1:35:08.528 --> 1:35:10.487
All right.
I'll go sign him out.

1:35:10.530 --> 1:35:11.706
BETH: Okay.

1:35:12.141 --> 1:35:13.620
Okay.

1:35:13.664 --> 1:35:15.013
Thank you.

1:35:18.582 --> 1:35:20.758
GIRL: That was when
time stood still.

1:35:20.802 --> 1:35:22.281
A moment that came to define

1:35:22.325 --> 1:35:24.414
that chapter
of my adolescence.

1:35:24.457 --> 1:35:28.723
And as I stood there
with my feet touching
the cold waters of Lake Owano,

1:35:28.766 --> 1:35:30.376
I knew I could never
go back again.

1:35:30.420 --> 1:35:32.291
Thank you.

1:35:32.335 --> 1:35:33.336
[APPLAUSE]

1:35:35.555 --> 1:35:37.514
SISTER CATHERINE: Let's have
another round of applause

1:35:37.557 --> 1:35:39.603
for our
Benchmark Exam finalists.

1:35:39.646 --> 1:35:40.647
[APPLAUSE]

1:35:45.435 --> 1:35:48.394
Without further ado,
may I present

1:35:48.438 --> 1:35:53.878
St. Agatha's graduating class
of 2020.

1:35:53.922 --> 1:35:56.054
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

