No.

1:37:18.354 --> 1:37:22.575
Hi. I'm Adam.

1:37:22.619 --> 1:37:25.622
-I'm here because...
-ADAM'S DARKNESS: Don't.

1:37:25.665 --> 1:37:28.973
-[OVERLAPPING DISTORTION]
-...I need my diploma.

1:37:29.017 --> 1:37:30.366
Without it...

1:37:30.409 --> 1:37:31.584
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Please, Adam.

1:37:31.628 --> 1:37:33.717
...I can't be the person
I wanna be.

1:37:34.500 --> 1:37:35.632
ADAM'S DARKNESS: Shut up.

1:37:35.675 --> 1:37:37.373
[DISTORTION CONTINUES]

1:37:37.416 --> 1:37:39.810
And that's because
I have schizophrenia.

1:37:46.861 --> 1:37:48.950
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
You're ruining
your mother's life, Adam.

1:37:52.127 --> 1:37:54.433
It's a chemical disorder...

1:37:54.477 --> 1:37:56.044
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
This is why your father left.

1:37:56.087 --> 1:37:57.219
...in the brain.

1:37:57.262 --> 1:37:59.917
And it makes you hear voices,

1:37:59.961 --> 1:38:03.442
and see things
that aren't there.

1:38:03.486 --> 1:38:05.096
It sucks.

1:38:05.140 --> 1:38:06.358
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
You're terrified.

1:38:06.402 --> 1:38:08.099
You could just Google it.

1:38:08.143 --> 1:38:09.884
ADAM'S DARKNESS: You will
always be terrified of me.

1:38:11.494 --> 1:38:13.800
I have people in my life

1:38:13.844 --> 1:38:16.891
who have been trying
to help me.

1:38:16.934 --> 1:38:20.590
People who've seen me
as more than an illness.

1:38:20.633 --> 1:38:22.374
But I pushed them away.

1:38:22.418 --> 1:38:28.728
I tried chasing this idea
of being normal.

1:38:28.772 --> 1:38:30.295
Whatever that means.

1:38:34.212 --> 1:38:36.823
Don't wanna end up
on the bathroom walls, right?

1:38:38.086 --> 1:38:40.175
ADAM'S DARKNESS:
You are who you are...

1:38:40.218 --> 1:38:41.263
[DISTORTING FADES]

1:38:45.049 --> 1:38:48.183
The Benchmark Exam asked us

1:38:48.226 --> 1:38:51.969
to write about
our greatest failure.

1:38:52.013 --> 1:38:56.104
And I wish that I could
read my essay right now,

1:38:56.147 --> 1:38:58.019
but it was based on a lie.

1:39:02.110 --> 1:39:06.027
My greatest failure,
hands down,

1:39:06.070 --> 1:39:09.726
has been hiding
from the ones I love.

1:39:11.858 --> 1:39:13.860
For believing
the voice in my head

1:39:13.904 --> 1:39:15.558
when it tells me...

1:39:17.168 --> 1:39:18.996
I'm ruining their lives.

1:39:21.781 --> 1:39:24.828
For believing it
when it tells me

1:39:24.871 --> 1:39:28.266
I'm too defective
to be loved by anyone.

1:39:30.573 --> 1:39:34.969
You made me feel
so many things.

1:39:38.885 --> 1:39:41.453
And I wasn't ready
to give that up.

1:39:43.978 --> 1:39:46.850
I'm sorry you had to expel me

1:39:46.893 --> 1:39:49.026
because I didn't fit
your picture of normalcy.

1:39:50.071 --> 1:39:51.942
But this is who I am.

1:39:54.336 --> 1:39:55.598
This is who I am.

1:39:56.512 --> 1:40:00.646
I'm Adam. I have an illness,

1:40:00.690 --> 1:40:03.823
but I'm not
the illness itself.

1:40:06.217 --> 1:40:07.262
[SIGHS]

1:40:08.872 --> 1:40:09.873
Okay.

1:40:17.359 --> 1:40:18.447
Thank you.

1:40:22.929 --> 1:40:24.714
[CHEERING]

1:40:26.716 --> 1:40:27.847
[INDISTINCT MURMURING]

1:40:41.165 --> 1:40:42.166
Adam.

1:40:57.442 --> 1:40:59.792
Hey, I'm... I'm sorry
about the hospital.

1:40:59.836 --> 1:41:00.924
No, I don't care
about the hospital.

1:41:00.967 --> 1:41:02.839
-I was just in a bad place.
-I know...

1:41:02.882 --> 1:41:04.362
And you have every right
to hate me.

1:41:04.406 --> 1:41:05.407
-I don't hate you, okay?
-ADAM: And if you don't wanna

1:41:05.450 --> 1:41:06.451
-talk to me...
-Stop!

1:41:07.583 --> 1:41:09.150
Is that why
you didn't tell me?

1:41:10.760 --> 1:41:12.892
Because you thought
that I was gonna leave?

1:41:14.590 --> 1:41:15.765
Hey.

1:41:16.418 --> 1:41:17.723
Right here.

1:41:17.767 --> 1:41:20.248
-No. I'm just...
-Then I don't...

1:41:20.291 --> 1:41:21.640
I'm always gonna see things,

1:41:21.684 --> 1:41:24.339
and hear things
that I shouldn't.

1:41:24.382 --> 1:41:26.558
And the drugs aren't always
gonna work.

1:41:26.602 --> 1:41:29.126
And I'm sorry, but I can't
put you through that.

1:41:32.042 --> 1:41:33.739
I'm sorry.

1:41:33.783 --> 1:41:34.958
Hey.

1:41:35.001 --> 1:41:37.656
Hey, hey.

1:41:37.700 --> 1:41:41.399
What makes you think you get
to make that decision
on your own?

1:41:41.443 --> 1:41:43.923
I wasn't mad
about the hospital.

1:41:43.967 --> 1:41:45.534
Or that you lied to me.

1:41:45.577 --> 1:41:46.578
ADAM: Then why?

1:41:48.319 --> 1:41:50.060
You didn't let me choose.

1:41:51.148 --> 1:41:53.716
You didn't give me
a chance to stay.

1:41:55.326 --> 1:41:56.675
Would you have?

1:41:59.635 --> 1:42:01.158
I love you.

1:42:03.813 --> 1:42:07.251
Hey, there's never been a more
explicit cue to kiss the girl.

1:42:15.868 --> 1:42:17.305
Okay.

1:42:18.349 --> 1:42:20.656
[REBECCA AND JOAQUIN
EXCLAIMING]

1:42:20.699 --> 1:42:22.310
JOAQUIN: Yes, yes, yes!

1:42:22.353 --> 1:42:24.573
ADAM: Am I gonna sit here
and tell you

1:42:24.616 --> 1:42:28.490
that things like
love and honesty
can cure crazy?

1:42:28.533 --> 1:42:29.926
No.

1:42:29.969 --> 1:42:32.189
But they sure can help.

1:42:32.233 --> 1:42:33.799
For example,

1:42:33.843 --> 1:42:36.933
my graduation speech earned
St. Agatha's enough shitty PR

1:42:36.976 --> 1:42:39.196
for them to give me
my diploma.

1:42:39.240 --> 1:42:41.807
That felt like a win
for honesty.

1:42:41.851 --> 1:42:43.940
And as for love,

1:42:44.854 --> 1:42:46.160
my mom was right.

1:42:47.900 --> 1:42:49.815
BETH: Tiny little fingers.

1:42:49.859 --> 1:42:51.600
ADAM: You have to
let people discover

1:42:51.643 --> 1:42:54.646
all your dark
and twisty places inside.

1:42:54.690 --> 1:42:56.909
She looks like you
a little bit.

1:42:56.953 --> 1:42:59.260
These big cheeks.

1:42:59.303 --> 1:43:00.522
-See these cheeks...
-[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

1:43:07.529 --> 1:43:10.009
REBECCA: [WHISPERING]
Adam, come over here.

1:43:17.321 --> 1:43:18.496
[WHISPERING STOPS]

1:43:18.540 --> 1:43:20.368
ADAM: Because those
are the people

1:43:20.411 --> 1:43:22.239
that can show you what's real

1:43:22.283 --> 1:43:25.416
when you can't
see that for yourself.

1:43:25.460 --> 1:43:27.462
It can be the beginning
of everything.

1:43:28.550 --> 1:43:30.116
If you let it.

1:43:30.160 --> 1:43:32.989
-Yeah. All right, no. Stop.
-BETH: You do.
